obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (37826)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37826&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Tripura Land Revenue`
  line `and Land Reforms Act, 1960.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the Union territory of Tripura.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date as the Administrator may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint; and different dates may be appointed for different areas and for different`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (37827)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37827&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,`
  line
  line `(a) "Administrator" means the Administrator of the Union territory of Tripura;`
  line
  line `(b) "agriculture" includes horticulture, the raising of annual or periodical crops or garden`
  line `produce, dairy farming, poultry farming, stock breeding, grazing and pisciculture;`
  line
  line `(c) "basic holding" means land used for agricultural purposes which is equal to two standard`
  line `acres in area;`
  line
  line `(d) "Collector" means the Collector of the district and includes any officer appointed by the`
  line `Administrator to exercise and perform all or any of the powers and functions of a Collector under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(e) "commencement of this Act", in relation to any provision, means the date specified in respect`
  line `of that provision in a notification under sub-section (3) of section 1;`
  line
  line `(f) "competent authority", in relation to any provision, means any officer appointed by the`
  line `Administrator to be the competent authority for the purpose of that provision;`
  line
  line `(g) "family" except in Chapter XIII means, in relation to a person, the wife or husband of such`
  line `person, his children, grandchildren, parents and brothers, and in the case of a Joint Hindu family, any`
  line `member of such family;`
  line
  line `(h) "family holding" means land used for agricultural purposes which is equal to 6.4 standard`
  line `acres in area;`
  line
  line `(i) "Government" means the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(j) "holding" means a parcel of land separately assessed to land revenue;`
  line
  line `(k) "improvement", in relation to any land, means any work which materially adds to the value of`
  line `the land and which is suitable to the land and consistent with the character thereof and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) the construction of tanks, wells, water channels and other works for the storage, supply`
  line `and distribution of water for agricultural purposes or for the use of man and cattle employed in`
  line agriculture;
  line
  line `(ii) the construction of works for the drainage of land or for the protection of land from floods`
  line `or from erosion or from other damage by water;`
  line
  line `(iii) the preparation of land for irrigation;`
  line
  line `(iv) the conversion of one-crop into two-crop land;`
  line
  line `(v) the reclaiming, clearing, enclosing, levelling or terracing of land used for agricultural`
  line purposes;
  line
  line `(vi) the erection on land or in the immediate vicinity thereof otherwise than on the village`
  line `site, of a building or house for the occupation of the under-raiyat, his family and servants or of a`
  line `cattle shed, a store-house or other construction for agricultural purposes or of any building`
  line `required for the convenient or profitable use or occupation of the land; and`
  line
  line `(vii) the renewal or reconstruction of any of the foregoing works or such alterations therein or`
  line `additions thereto as are not of the nature of ordinary repairs;`
  line
  line `(l) "minor" means a person who is deemed not to have attained majority under the`
  line `Indian Majority Act, 1875 (9 of 1875);`
  line
  line `(m) "Official Gazette" means the Tripura Gazette;`
  line
  line `(n) "pay", "payable" and "payment", used with reference to rent, include "deliver", "deliverable"`
  line `and "delivery";`
  line
  line `(o) "person under disability" means--`
  line
  line `(i) a widow;`
  line
  line `(ii) a minor;`
  line
  line `(iii) a woman who is unmarried or who, if married, is divorced or judicially separated from`
  line `her husband or whose husband is a person falling under item (iv) or (v);`
  line
  line `(iv) a member of the Armed Forces of the Union;`
  line
  line `(v) a person incapable of cultivating land by reason of some physical or mental disability;`
  line
  line `(p) "personal cultivation", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means`
  line `cultivation by a person on his own account--`
  line
  line `(i) by his own labour, or`
  line
  line `(ii) by the labour of any member of his family, or`
  line
  line `(iii) by servants or by hired labour on wages, payable in cash or in kind but not as a share of`
  line `produce, under his personal supervision or the personal supervision of any member of his family;`
  line
  line `Explanation I.-- Land shall not be deemed to be cultivated under the personal supervision of a`
  line `person or a member of his family unless such person or member resides in the village in which the`
  line `land is situated or in a nearby village situated within a distance to be prescribed, during the major part`
  line `of the agricultural season;`
  line
  line `Explanation II.-- In the case of a person under disability, supervision by a paid employee on`
  line `behalf of such person shall be deemed to be personal supervision;`
  line
  line `(q) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(r) "public purpose" includes a purpose connected with allotment of land to cultivators,`
  line `under-raiyats ejected as a result of resumption, land-less agricultural workers or co-operative farming`
  line societies;
  line
  line `(s) "raiyat" means a person who owns land for purposes of agriculture paying land revenue to the`
  line `Government and includes the successors-in-interest of such person;`
  line
  line `(t) "rent" means whatever is lawfully payable, in money or in kind, or partly in money and partly`
  line `in kind, whether as a fixed quantity of produce or as a share of the produce, on account of the use or`
  line `occupation of land or on account of any right in land but shall not include land revenue;`
  line
  line `(u) "standard acre" means one acre of "lunga" or "nal" or three acres of "tilla" land;`
  line
  line `(v) "under-raiyat" means a person who cultivates or holds the land of a raiyat under an agreement,`
  line `express or implied, on condition of paying therefor rent in cash or in kind or delivering a share of the`
  line `produce and includes a person who cultivates or holds land of a raiyat under the system generally`
  line `known as "bhag", "adhi" or "barga";`
  line
  line `(w) "village" means any tract of land which, before the commencement of this Act, was`
  line `recognised as or was declared to be a village under any law for the time being in force or which may`
  line `after such commencement be recognised as a village at any settlement or which the Administrator`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare to be a village;`
  line
  line `(x) "year" means the agricultural year commencing on such date as the Administrator may, in the`
  line `case of any specified area, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (37828)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Power to create, alter or abolish districts, sub-divisions, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37828&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, with`
  line `the previous concurrence of the Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, divide the Union`
  line `territory of Tripura into one or more districts, and may similarly divide any district into sub-divisions,`
  line `circles and tehsils, and may alter the limits of, or abolish, any district, sub-division, circle or tehsil.`
  line
  line `(2) The districts, sub-divisions, circles and tehsils existing at the commencement of this Act shall`
  line `continue respectively to be the districts, sub-divisions, circles and tehsils under this Act unless otherwise`
  line `provided under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (37829)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of revenue officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37829&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Government or such other officer as may be authorised`
  line `by the Government in this behalf may appoint the following classes of revenue officers, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) Collector,`
  line
  line `(b) director of settlement and land records,`
  line
  line `(c) sub-divisional officers,`
  line
  line `(d) survey and settlement officers,`
  line
  line `(e) assistant survey and settlement officers,`
  line
  line `(f) circle officers,`
  line
  line `(g) revenue inspectors,`
  line
  line `(h) tehsildars,`
  line
  line `(i) village accountants and such other village officers and servants as may be specified by rules`
  line `made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (37830)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Collector and certain other revenue officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37830&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each district shall be placed under the charge`
  line `of a Collector who shall be in charge of the revenue administration of the district and exercise the powers`
  line `and discharge the duties of the Collector under this Act or any other law for the time being in force and`
  line `shall exercise so far as is consistent therewith such other powers of superintendence and control within`
  line `the district and over the officers subordinate to him as may from time to time be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Each sub-division shall be placed under the charge of a sub-divisional officer.`
  line
  line `(3) Each circle or tehsil shall be placed under the charge of a circle officer or a tehsildar, as the case`
  line `may be.`
  line
  line `(4) The duties and powers of the sub-divisional officers, the circle officers and other revenue officers`
  line `shall be such as may be imposed or conferred on them by or under this Act or any other law in force for`
  line `the time being or any general or special order of the Administrator published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (37831)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Settlement officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37831&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The officers specified in items (b), (d) and (e) of section 4 shall have power`
  line `to take cognizance of all matters connected with the survey of land and the settlement of the revenue-rates`
  line `and the preparation and maintenance of land records and other registers and shall exercise all such powers`
  line `and perform all such duties as may be prescribed by or under this Act or by any general or special order`
  line `of the Administrator published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (37832)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Subordination of revenue officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37832&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `All revenue officers shall be subordinate to the`
  line `Administrator and all revenue officers in the district or a sub-division shall be sub ordinate to the`
  line `Collector or the sub-divisional officer, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (37833)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Combination of offices.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37833&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for the Administrator to appoint one and the same`
  line `person to any two or more of the offices provided for in this Chapter, to make any appointment by virtue`
  line `of office and also to confer on any officer of the Government all or any of the powers and duties of any of`
  line `the revenue officers including the Collector.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (37834)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Notification of appointments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37834&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `All appointments made under this Chapter except appointments`
  line `of revenue inspectors, tehsildars and village accountants and other village officers and servants shall be`
  line `notified in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (37835)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Seals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37835&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator shall, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify the revenue officers who shall use a seal and also the size and description of the seal which each`
  line `such officer shall use.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (37836)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Title of Government to lands, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37836&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) All lands, public roads, lanes and paths and bridges,`
  line `ditches, dikes, and fences on or beside the same, the beds of rivers, streams, nallas, lakes and tanks, and`
  line `all canals and water courses, and all standing and flowing water, and all rights in or over the same or`
  line `appertaining thereto, which are not the property of any person, are and are hereby declared to be the`
  line `property of the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Unless it is otherwise expressly provided in the terms of a grant made by the Government, the`
  line `right to mines, quarries, minerals and mineral products including mineral oil, natural gas and petroleum`
  line `shall vest in the Government, and it shall have all the powers necessary for the proper enjoyment of such`
  line rights.
  line
  line `(3) Where any property or any right in or over any property is claimed by or on behalf of the`
  line `Government, or by any person as against the Government and the claim is disputed, such dispute shall be`
  line `decided by the Collector whose order shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, be final.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by an order made under sub-section (3) or in appeal or revision therefrom`
  line `may institute a civil suit to contest the order within a period of six months from the date of such order and`
  line `the decision of the civil court shall be binding on the parties.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (37837)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Right to trees, forests, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37837&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The right to all trees, jungles or other natural products growing`
  line `on land set apart for forest reserves and to all trees, brush wood, jungle or other natural product, wherever`
  line `growing, except in so far as the same may be the property of any person, vests in the Government, and`
  line `such trees, brush wood, jungle or other natural product shall be preserved or disposed of in such manner`
  line `as may be prescribed, keeping in view the interests of the people in the area with regard to the user of the`
  line `natural products.`
  line
  line `(2) All road side trees which have been planted and reared by or under the orders or at the expense of`
  line `the Government and all trees which have been planted and reared at the expense of local authorities by`
  line `the side of any road belonging to the Government vest in the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (37838)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Assignment of land for special purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37838&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Subject to rules made in this behalf under this Act,`
  line `the Collector may set apart land belonging to the Government for pasturage for the village cattle, for`
  line `forest reserves or for any other purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (37839)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Allotment of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37839&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Collector may allot land belonging to the Government for`
  line `agricultural purposes or for construction of dwelling houses, in accordance with such rules as may be`
  line `made in this behalf under this Act; and such rules may provide for allotment of land to persons evicted`
  line `under section 15.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator shall have power--`
  line
  line `(a) to allot any such land for the purpose of an industry or for any purpose of public utility on`
  line `such conditions as may be prescribed, or`
  line
  line `(b) to entrust the management of any such land or any rights therein to the gram panchayat of the`
  line `village established under any law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (37840)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Unauthorised occupation of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37840&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who occupies or continues to occupy any`
  line `land belonging to Government without lawful authority shall be regarded as a trespasser and may be`
  line `summarily evicted therefrom by the competent authority and any building or other construction erected or`
  line `anything deposited on such land, if not removed within such reasonable time as such authority may from`
  line `time to time fix for the purpose, shall be liable to be forfeited to the Government and to be disposed of in`
  line `such manner as the competent authority may direct:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority may, in lieu of ordering the forfeiture of any such building or`
  line `other construction, order the demolition of the whole or any part thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) Such trespasser shall also be liable by way of penalty to pay a sum which may extend to six times`
  line `the annual assessment on such land as may be specified by the competent authority and such sum shall be`
  line `recoverable in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `(3) Upon payment of the penalty referred to in sub-section (2), the trespasser shall have the right of`
  line `tending, gathering and removing any ungathered crops.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (37841)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Liability of land to land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37841&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) All lands, to whatever purpose applied, are liable to`
  line `payment of land revenue to the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Administrator may exempt any land from the liability to such payment by means of a special`
  line `grant or contract or in accordance with any law for the time being in force or the rules made under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (37842)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Alluvial lands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37842&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `All alluvial lands, newly formed islands, or abandoned river beds, which vest`
  line `under any law for the time being in force in any holder of land shall be subject in respect of liability to`
  line `land revenue to the same privileges, conditions and restrictions as are applicable to the original holding by`
  line `virtue of which such lands, islands or river beds vest in the said holder, but no revenue shall be leviable in`
  line `respect of any such lands, islands or river beds unless the area of the same exceeds one acre.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (37843)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Land revenue in case of diluvion.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37843&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Every holder of land paying land revenue in respect thereof`
  line `shall be entitled, subject to such rules as may be made in this behalf, to a decrease of assessment if any`
  line `portion thereof, not being less than one acre in extent, is lost by diluvion.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (37844)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Assessment of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37844&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The assessment of land revenue on any land shall be made, or`
  line `shall be deemed to have been made, with respect to the use of the land`
  line
  line `(a) for purposes of agriculture;`
  line
  line `(b) for industrial or commercial purposes;`
  line
  line `(c) as sites for dwelling houses;`
  line
  line `(d) for any other purpose.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, land assessed for use for any one purpose is diverted to any other purpose, the land`
  line `revenue payable upon such land shall, notwithstanding that the term for which the assessment may have`
  line `been fixed has not expired, be liable to be altered and assessed at a different rate in accordance with the`
  line `rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (37845)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Diversion of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37845&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person holding land for any purpose wishes to divert such land or`
  line `any part thereof to any other purpose except agriculture, he shall apply for permission to the competent`
  line `authority who may, subject to the provisions of this section and to the rules made under this Act, refuse`
  line `permission or grant it on such conditions as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) Permission to divert may be refused by the competent authority only on the ground that the`
  line `diversion is likely to cause a public nuisance or that it is not in the interest of the general public or that the`
  line `holder is unable or unwilling to comply with the conditions that may be imposed under sub-section (3).`
  line
  line `(3) Conditions may be imposed on diversion for the following objects and no others, namely, in order`
  line `to secure the public health, safety and convenience, and in the case of land which is to be used as building`
  line `sites, in order to secure in addition that the dimensions, arrangement and accessibility of the sites are`
  line `adequate for the health and convenience of occupiers or are suitable to the locality.`
  line
  line `(4) If any land has been diverted without permission by the holder or by any other person with or`
  line `without the consent of the holder, the competent authority, on receiving information thereof, may impose`
  line `on the person responsible for the diversion a penalty not exceeding one hundred rupees, and may proceed`
  line `in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (1) as if an application for permission to divert has been`
  line made.
  line
  line `(5) If any land has been diverted in contravention of an order passed or of a condition imposed under`
  line `any of the foregoing sub-sections, the competent authority may serve a notice on the person responsible`
  line `for such contravention, directing him, within a reasonable period to be stated in the notice, to use the land`
  line `for its original purpose or to observe the condition; and such notice may require such person to remove`
  line `any structure, to fill up any excavation, or to take such other steps as may be required in order that the`
  line `land may be used for its original purpose, or that the condition may be satisfied. The competent authority`
  line `may also impose on such person a penalty not exceeding one hundred rupees for such contravention, and`
  line `a further penalty not exceeding four rupees for each day during which such contravention continues.`
  line
  line `(6) If any person served with a notice under sub-section (5), fails within the period stated in the notice`
  line `to take the steps ordered by the competent authority under that sub-section, the competent authority may`
  line `itself take such steps or cause them to be taken; and any cost incurred in so doing shall be recoverable`
  line `from such person in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- "Diversion" in this section means using land assessed to one purpose for any other`
  line `purpose, but using land for the purpose of agriculture where it is assessed with reference to any other`
  line `purpose shall not be deemed to be diversion.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (37846)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Remission or suspension of revenue on failure of crops.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37846&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator may, in`
  line `accordance with the rules made in this behalf under this Act, grant a remission or suspension of land`
  line `revenue in years in which crops have failed in any area.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (37847)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Responsibility for payment of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37847&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The following persons shall be primarily`
  line `liable for the payment of land revenue assessed on land, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the person to whom the land belongs;`
  line
  line `(b) the under-raiyat or any other person in possession of the land, provided that such under-raiyat`
  line `or other person shall be entitled to credit from the owner of the land for the amount paid by him;`
  line
  line `(2) Where there are two or more persons liable to pay land revenue under sub-section (1), all of them`
  line `shall be jointly and severally liable for its payment`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (37848)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Receipt for land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37848&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Every revenue officer receiving payment of land revenue shall, at`
  line `the time when such payment is received by him, give a written receipt for the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (37849)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Definitions of “revenue survey”, “settlement” and “term of settlement”.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37849&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `The operations`
  line `carried out in accordance with the provisions of this Chapter in order to determine or revise the land`
  line `revenue payable on lands in any local area are called a "revenue survey", the results of the operations are`
  line `called a "settlement" and the period during which such results are to be in force is called the "term of`
  line `settlement".`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (37850)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Inquiry into profits of agriculture.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37850&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, the Administrator shall take steps to institute and shall cause to be constantly maintained, in`
  line `accordance with the rules made under this Act, an inquiry into the profits of agriculture and into the value`
  line `of land used for agricultural and non-agricultural purposes.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of determining the profits of agriculture, the following matters shall be taken into`
  line `account in estimating the cost of cultivation, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the depreciation of stock and buildings;`
  line
  line `(b) the money equivalent of the labour and supervision by the cultivator and his family;`
  line
  line `(c) all other expenses usually incurred in the cultivation of the land which is under inquiry; and`
  line
  line `(d) interest on the cost of buildings and stock, on all expenditure for seed and manure and on the`
  line `cost of agricultural operations paid for in cash.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (37851)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Revenue survey.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37851&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Whenever the Administrator thinks it expedient so to do, he may, with the`
  line `approval of the Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct the revenue survey of any local`
  line `area with a view to the settlement of the land revenue and to the preparation of a record of rights`
  line `connected therewith or the revision of any existing settlement or record of rights.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (37852)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to require assistance from landholders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37852&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `A survey officer deputed to conduct or take`
  line `part in any revenue survey may, by special order or by general notice to be published in the prescribed`
  line `manner, require the attendance of holders of lands to assist in the measurement or classification of the`
  line `lands to which the revenue survey extends and, when hired labour is employed for purposes incidental to`
  line `the revenue survey, may assess and apportion the cost thereof on the lands surveyed, for collection as land`
  line `revenue due on such lands.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (37853)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Survey numbers and villages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37853&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the rules made in this behalf under this Act, the`
  line `survey officer may--`
  line
  line `(a) divide the lands to which the revenue survey extends into villages and the villages into plots`
  line `and survey numbers; and`
  line
  line `(b) recognise the existing villages and survey numbers, reconstitute them or form new survey`
  line numbers.
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (37854)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Division of survey numbers into sub-divisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37854&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `The survey officer may sub-divide survey`
  line `numbers into as many sub-divisions as may be required in the manner prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (37855)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Determination of revenue-rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37855&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator may at any time direct the determination`
  line `or the revision of the revenue-rates for all lands in any area of which a revenue survey has been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (37856)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Preparation of statistical and fiscal records.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37856&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the survey officer or the`
  line `settlement officer on the occasion of making or revising a settlement of land revenue to prepare a register`
  line `to be called the "settlement register", showing the area and assessment of each survey number, with any`
  line `other particulars that may be prescribed, and other records in accordance with such orders as may from`
  line `time to time be made in this behalf by the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (37857)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Revenue-rates how determined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37857&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of determining the revenue-rates, the`
  line `settlement officer may divide any area into units and in forming such units, he shall have regard to the`
  line `physical features, agricultural and economic conditions and trade facilities and communications; and shall`
  line `then determine the revenue-rates for different classes of lands in each such unit in the manner and`
  line `according to the principles prescribed and in particular, in the case of agricultural land, to the profits of`
  line `agriculture, to the consideration paid for leases, to the sale prices of land and to the principal monies on`
  line `mortgages and in the case of non-agricultural land, to the value of the land for the purpose for which it is`
  line held.
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (37858)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Publication of table of revenue-rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37858&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `(1) The settlement officer shall prepare a table of`
  line `revenue-rates in the prescribed form and publish it in the prescribed manner for the prescribed period.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person objecting to any entry in the table of revenue-rates may present a petition in writing to`
  line `the settlement officer within the prescribed period and the settlement officer shall consider such`
  line `objections after giving a hearing to the objector.`
  line
  line `(3) The settlement officer shall submit the table of revenue-rates to the Administrator together with a`
  line `summary of objections, if any, his decisions on such objections and a statement of the grounds in support`
  line `of his proposals.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (37859)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Confirmation of the table of revenue-rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37859&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may confirm the table of`
  line `revenue-rates submitted to him by the settlement officer with such modifications, if any, as he may`
  line `consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) The table of revenue-rates confirmed under sub-section (1) shall be finally published in the`
  line `Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (37860)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Rates of revenue to form part of settlement register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37860&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The table of revenue-rates published`
  line `under section 34 shall be incorporated in and form part of the settlement register of the village.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (37861)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Introduction of revenue-rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37861&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `When the revenue-rates are determined under this Chapter in`
  line `respect of any area, such rates shall take effect from the beginning of the year next after the date of final`
  line `publication of the table of revenue-rates under section 34.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (37862)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Duration of revenue-rates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37862&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the table of revenue-rates for any area has been finally`
  line `published, the rates specified therein shall remain in force for a period of thirty years.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) revenue-rates may be altered or revised in any year after the expiry of every ten years from the`
  line `date on which the table of revenue-rates was introduced, in such manner and to such extent as may be`
  line prescribed;
  line
  line `(b) when the circumstances of a local area are such that a fresh determination of the revenue-rates`
  line `is in the opinion of the Administrator inexpedient, he may extend the term of settlement by such`
  line `further period as he may think necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (37863)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Assessment on holdings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37863&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The settlement officer shall calculate the assessment on each`
  line `holding in accordance with the revenue-rates confirmed and finally published under section 34 and such`
  line `assessment shall be the fair assessment.`
  line
  line `(2) The settlement officer shall have the power to make fair assessment on all lands whatsoever to`
  line `which the revenue survey extends, whether such lands are held with liability to pay full land revenue or`
  line `land revenue at concessional rates or are held revenue free.`
  line
  line `(3) The fair assessment of all lands shall be calculated in accordance with rules made in this behalf`
  line `and having regard to the following principles, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) no regard shall be had to any claim to hold land on privileged terms;`
  line
  line `(b) regard shall be had in the case of agricultural land to the profits of agriculture, to the`
  line `consideration paid for leases, to the sale prices of land and to the principal monies on mortgages, and`
  line `in the case of non-agricultural land, to the value of the land for the purpose for which it is held;`
  line
  line `(c) where any improvement has been effected at any time in any holding held for the purpose of`
  line `agriculture by or at the expense of the holder thereof, the fair assessment of such holding shall be`
  line `fixed as if the improvement had not been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (37864)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Additional assessment for water advantages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37864&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Chapter, the Administrator may direct that any land in respect of which the rate of revenue has been`
  line `determined shall be liable to be assessed to additional land revenue during the term of the settlement for`
  line `additional advantages accruing to it from water received on account of irrigation works or improvements`
  line `in existing irrigation works completed after the table of revenue-rates came into force and not effected by`
  line `or at the expense of the holder of the land.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (37865)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Continuance of survey operations and rates in force at commencement of Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37865&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `otwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, all survey operations commenced under any`
  line `law for the time being in force and continuing at the commencement of this Act shall be deemed to have`
  line `been commenced and to be continuing under the provisions of this Chapter, and all revenue-rates in force`
  line `at such commencement shall be deemed to have been determined and introduced in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter and shall remain in force until the introduction of revised revenue-rates; and`
  line `such revised revenue-rates may be introduced at any time, notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 37.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (37866)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Power of Collector to correct errors, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37866&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) The powers and duties exercisable by the`
  line `officers referred to in section 6 may also be exercised, during the term of settlement, by the Collector or`
  line `such other revenue officer as may be specified by the Administrator for the purpose by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector may at any time during the term of settlement correct any error in the area`
  line `or the assessment of any survey number or sub-division due to a mistake of survey or arithmetical`
  line `miscalculation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no arrears of land revenue shall become payable by reason of such correction.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (37867)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Preparation of record of rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37867&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the survey officer to prepare a record of`
  line `rights for each village showing the area of each survey number and other particulars and any other record`
  line `or register, in accordance with the rules made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (37868)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Publication of the record of rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37868&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `(1) When a record of rights has been prepared, the survey`
  line `officer shall publish a draft of the record in such manner and for such period as may be prescribed and`
  line `shall receive and consider any objections which may be made during the period of such publication, to`
  line `any entry therein or to any omission therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) When all objections have been considered and disposed of in accordance with the rules made in`
  line `this behalf, the survey officer shall cause the record to be finally published in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(3) Every entry in the record of rights as finally published shall, until, the contrary is proved, be`
  line `presumed to be correct.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (37869)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts to decide disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37869&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `The civil courts shall have jurisdiction to`
  line `decide any dispute to which the Government is not a party relating to any right or entry which is recorded`
  line `in the record of rights.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (37870)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Correction of bona fide mistake in register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37870&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The survey officer may, on application made to`
  line `him in this behalf or on his own motion, within one year from the date of final publication of the record of`
  line `rights, correct any entry in such record which he is satisfied has been made owing to a bona fide mistake.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (37871)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Register of mutations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37871&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be maintained for every village a register of mutations in`
  line `such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person acquiring by succession, survivorship, inheritance, partition, purchase, gift, mortgage,`
  line `lease or otherwise any right in land or, where such person acquiring the right is a minor or otherwise`
  line `disqualified, his guardian or other person having charge of his property, shall report his acquisition of`
  line `such right to the village accountant within three months from the date of such acquisition and the village`
  line `accountant shall give at once a written acknowledgement in the prescribed form for such report to the`
  line `person making it.`
  line
  line `(3) The village accountant shall enter the substance of every report made to him under sub-section (2)`
  line `in the register of mutations and also make an entry therein respecting the acquisition of any right of the`
  line `kind mentioned in sub-section (2) which he has reason to believe to have taken place and of which a`
  line `report has not be made under the said sub-section and, at the same time, shall post up a complete copy of`
  line `the entry in a conspicuous place in the village and shall give written intimation to all persons appearing`
  line `from the record of rights or the register of mutations to be interested in the mutations and to any other`
  line `person whom he has reason to believe to be interested therein.`
  line
  line `(4) Should any objection to an entry made under sub-section (3) in the register of mutations be made`
  line `either orally or in writing to the village accountant, he shall enter the particulars of the objection in the`
  line `register of disputed cases and shall at once give a written acknowledgement in the prescribed form for the`
  line `objection to the person making it.`
  line
  line `(5) The objections made under sub-section (4) shall be decided on the basis of possession by the`
  line `competent authority and orders disposing of objections entered in the register of disputed cases shall be`
  line `recorded in the register of mutations by the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(6) After the entries in the register of mutations have been tested and found correct, the entries shall`
  line `be transferred to the record of rights and shall be certified by such officer as may be prescribed in this`
  line behalf.
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (37872)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Penalty for neglect to afford information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37872&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `The Collector may, if he is of opinion that any`
  line `person has wilfully neglected to make the report required by section 46 within the prescribed period,`
  line `impose on such person a penalty not exceeding twenty-five rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (37873)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Assistance in preparation of maps.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37873&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `Subject to rules made under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) any revenue officer may, for the purpose of preparing or revising any map or plan required for`
  line `or in connection with any record or register under this Chapter, exercise any of the powers of the`
  line `survey officer under section 27 except the power of assessing the cost of hired labour; and`
  line
  line `(b) any revenue officer not below the rank of sub-divisional officer may assess the cost of the`
  line `preparation or revision of such maps or plans and all expenses incidental thereto, and such costs and`
  line `expenses shall be recoverable in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (37874)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Certified copies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37874&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `Certified copies of entries in the record of rights may be granted by such`
  line `officers and on payment of such fees as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (37875)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Maps and other records open to inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37875&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `ubject to such rules and on payment of such`
  line `fees, if any, as may be prescribed, all maps and land records shall be open to inspection by the public`
  line `during office hours, and certified extracts therefrom or certified copies thereof may be given to all persons`
  line `applying for the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (37876)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Power to transfer duty of maintaining maps and records to settlement officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37876&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `When a local`
  line `area is under settlement, the duty of maintaining the maps and records may, under the orders of the`
  line `Administrator, be transferred from the Collector to the settlement officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (37877)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Determination of village boundaries.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37877&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The boundaries of villages, survey numbers,`
  line `sub-divisions and fields shall be fixed, and all disputes relating thereto shall be determined, by survey`
  line `officers or by such other officers as may be appointed by the Administrator for the purpose, in accordance`
  line `with the rules made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (37878)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Effect of settlement of boundary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37878&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The settlement of a boundary under this Chapter shall be`
  line determinative--
  line
  line `(a) of the proper position of the boundary line or boundary marks; and`
  line
  line `(b) of the rights of the landholders on either side of the boundary fixed in respect of the land`
  line `adjudged to appertain, or not to appertain, to their respective holdings.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a boundary has been so fixed, the Collector may at any time summarily evict any`
  line `landholder who is wrongfully in possession of any land which has been adjudged in the settlement of a`
  line `boundary not to appertain to his holding or to the holding of any person through or under whom he`
  line claims.
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (37879)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Construction and repair of boundary marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37879&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for any survey officer`
  line `authorised in this behalf to specify, or cause to be constructed, laid out, maintained or repaired, boundary`
  line `marks of villages or survey numbers or sub-divisions and to assess all charges incurred thereby on the`
  line `holders or others having an interest therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (37880)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Description of boundary marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37880&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The boundary marks shall be of such description and shall be`
  line `constructed, laid out, maintained or repaired in such manner and shall be of such dimensions and`
  line `materials as may, subject to the rules made under this Act, be determined by the Collector or other officer`
  line `appointed for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (37881)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Responsibilities for maintaining boundary marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37881&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `Every landholder shall be responsible for`
  line `the maintenance an good repair of the boundary marks of his holding and for any charge reasonably`
  line `incurred on account of the same by the revenue officers in case of alteration, removal or disrepair. It shall`
  line `be the duty of the village officers and servants to prevent the destruction or unauthorised alteration of the`
  line `village boundary marks.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (37882)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Collector to have charge of boundary marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37882&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `After the introduction of survey and settlement`
  line `in a district, the charge of the boundary marks shall devolve on the Collector and it shall be his duty to`
  line `take measures for their construction, laying out, maintenance and repair.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (37883)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Penalty for injuring boundary marks.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37883&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `Any person wilfully erasing, removing or injuring a`
  line `boundary mark shall be liable to such penalty not exceeding fifty rupees as the competent authority may`
  line impose.
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (37884)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Land revenue to be first charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37884&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `Land revenue assessed on any land shall be the first charge`
  line `on that land and on the crops, rents and profits thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_59_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (37885)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Payment of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37885&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `Land revenue shall be payable at such times, in such instalments, to`
  line `such persons, and at such places, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (37886)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Arrear of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37886&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any instalment of land revenue or part thereof which is not paid`
  line `on the due date shall become an arrear of land revenue and the person responsible for the payment shall`
  line `become a defaulter.`
  line
  line `(2) A statement of account certified by the circle officer shall, for the purpose of this Chapter, be`
  line `conclusive evidence of the existence of the arrear, of its amount and of the person who is the defaulter:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall prejudice the right of such person to make payment`
  line `under protest and to question the correctness of the account in separate proceedings before the competent`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (37887)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Recovery of Arrears.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37887&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `An arrear of land revenue may be recovered by any one or more of the`
  line `following processes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) by serving a written notice of demand on the defaulter;`
  line
  line `(b) by distraint and sale of the defaulter's movable property, including the produce of the land;`
  line
  line `(c) by the attachment and sale of the defaulters immovable property.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (37888)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Notice of demand.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37888&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `The form and contents of the notice of demand and the officers by whom`
  line `such notices shall be issued shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_64:
  sectionId (37889)
  sectionNo (64)
  orderNo 64
  title `Distraint and sale of movable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_64_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37889&sectionno=64&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_64_content:
  string
  line `(1) The distraint and sale of the movable property of`
  line `a defaulter shall be made by such officers or class of officers, in such manner and in accordance with such`
  line `procedure, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to authorise the distraint or sale of any property which,`
  line `under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), is exempt from attachment or sale in execution of a`
  line `decree or of any article set aside exclusively for religious use.`
obj_root_law_sections_64_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_65:
  sectionId (37890)
  sectionNo (65)
  orderNo 65
  title `Sale of immovable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_65_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37890&sectionno=65&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_65_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the Collector is of opinion that the processes referred`
  line `to in clauses (a) and (b) of section 62 are not sufficient for the recovery of an arrear, he may, in addition`
  line `to or instead of any of those processes, cause the land in respect of which such arrear is due to be attached`
  line `and sold in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector may also cause the right, title and interest of the defaulter in any other immovable`
  line `property to be similarly attached and sold.`
obj_root_law_sections_65_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_66:
  sectionId (37891)
  sectionNo (66)
  orderNo 66
  title `Notice of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_66_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37891&sectionno=66&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_66_content:
  string
  line `(1) Before effecting the sale of any land or other immovable property under the`
  line `provisions of this Chapter, the Collector or other officer empowered in this behalf shall issue such notices`
  line `and proclamations, in such form, in such manner and containing such particulars, as may be prescribed;`
  line `the notices and proclamations shall also be published in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notice or proclamation issued under sub-section (1) shall be served on the`
  line defaulter.
obj_root_law_sections_66_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_67:
  sectionId (37892)
  sectionNo (67)
  orderNo 67
  title `Sale to be by auction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_67_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37892&sectionno=67&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_67_content:
  string
  line `All sales of property, movable or immovable, under this Chapter shall be`
  line `by public auction held in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_67_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_68:
  sectionId (37893)
  sectionNo (68)
  orderNo 68
  title `Prohibition to bid at auction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_68_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37893&sectionno=68&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_68_content:
  string
  line `No officer having any duty to perform in connection with any`
  line `such sale and no person employed by or subordinate to such officer shall, either directly or indirectly, bid`
  line `for or acquire any property except on behalf of the Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_68_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_69:
  sectionId (37894)
  sectionNo (69)
  orderNo 69
  title `Sale of perishables.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_69_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37894&sectionno=69&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_69_content:
  string
  line `Perishable articles shall be sold by auction with the least possible delay`
  line `and such sale shall be finally concluded by the officer conducting the sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_69_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_70:
  sectionId (37895)
  sectionNo (70)
  orderNo 70
  title `Sales not to be excessive.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_70_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37895&sectionno=70&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_70_content:
  string
  line `Every sale of property, movable or immovable, under the provisions`
  line `of this Chapter shall, as far as may be practicable, be proportionate to the amount of the arrear of land`
  line `revenue to be recovered together with the interest thereon and the expenses of attachment and sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_70_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_71:
  sectionId (37896)
  sectionNo (71)
  orderNo 71
  title `Deposit by purchaser of immovable property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_71_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37896&sectionno=71&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_71_content:
  string
  line `In all cases of sale of immovable property, the`
  line `party who is declared to be the purchaser shall be required to deposit immediately 25 per cent. of the`
  line `amount of his bid, and the balance within fifteen days of the date of sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_71_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_72:
  sectionId (37897)
  sectionNo (72)
  orderNo 72
  title `Failure to make deposit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_72_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37897&sectionno=72&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_72_content:
  string
  line `(1) In default of the payment of deposit referred to in section 71, the`
  line `property shall be put up for re-sale and the expenses incurred in connection with the first sale shall be`
  line `borne by the defaulting bidder.`
  line
  line `(2) In default of payment of the balance of the bid amount within the period prescribed in section 71,`
  line `the deposit after defraying therefrom the expenses of the sale shall be forfeited to the Government and the`
  line `property shall be re-sold.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the proceeds of the re-sale are less than the price bid by such defaulting purchaser, the`
  line `difference shall also be recoverable from him in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_72_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_73:
  sectionId (37898)
  sectionNo (73)
  orderNo 73
  title `Setting aside sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_73_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37898&sectionno=73&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_73_content:
  string
  line `Where immovable property has been sold under this Chapter, the defaulter,`
  line `or any person owning such property or holding an interest therein, may, at any time, within thirty days of`
  line `the date of sale or within such further period not exceeding thirty days as the Collector may for sufficient`
  line `cause allow, apply in the prescribed manner to the Collector to have the sale set aside--`
  line
  line `(a) on the ground of some material irregularity or mistake or fraud resulting in substantial loss or`
  line `injury to him, or`
  line
  line `(b) on his depositing in the Collectors office the amount of the arrear specified in the`
  line `proclamation of sale, the cost of the sale and for payment to the purchaser, a sum equal to 5 per cent.`
  line `of the purchase money.`
obj_root_law_sections_73_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_74:
  sectionId (37899)
  sectionNo (74)
  orderNo 74
  title `Confirmation of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_74_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37899&sectionno=74&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_74_content:
  string
  line `If, on the expiration of thirty days from the date of sale of any`
  line `immovable property or of the further period, if any, allowed under section 73, no application has been`
  line `made for setting aside the sale, or if any such application has been made and rejected, the Collector shall`
  line `make an order confirming the sale unless, for reasons to be recorded, the Collector sets aside the sale`
  line `notwithstanding that no application therefor has been made.`
obj_root_law_sections_74_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_75:
  sectionId (37900)
  sectionNo (75)
  orderNo 75
  title Refunds.
  content obj_root_law_sections_75_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37900&sectionno=75&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_75_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Collector shall order the refund and payment to me purchaser, of`
  line
  line `(a) the amounts deposited by him under section 71; and`
  line
  line `(b) the sum equal to 5 per cent. of the purchase money deposited under clause (b) of section 73;`
  line `if the sale is not confirmed or is set aside.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector shall order the refund and payment of all the moneys deposited under clause (b) of`
  line `section 73 to the person who made the deposit, if the sale is confirmed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Collector may set off the whole or any part of any such moneys against any arrears`
  line `of land revenue or any other arrear recoverable as an arrear of land revenue, which may be outsantanding`
  line `against the person who made the deposit.`
obj_root_law_sections_75_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_76:
  sectionId (37901)
  sectionNo (76)
  orderNo 76
  title `Certificate of purchase.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_76_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37901&sectionno=76&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_76_content:
  string
  line `When a sale held under this Chapter is confirmed, the Collector shall`
  line `put the person declared to be the purchaser in possession of the property and shall grant him a certificate`
  line `in the prescribed form to the effect that he has purchased the property specified therein, and such`
  line `certificate shall be deemed to be a valid transfer of such property.`
obj_root_law_sections_76_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_77:
  sectionId (37902)
  sectionNo (77)
  orderNo 77
  title `Application of proceeds of sale.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_77_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37902&sectionno=77&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_77_content:
  string
  line `The proceeds of the sale of any property under this Chapter`
  line `shall be applied in defraying the expenses of the sale which shall be determined in the prescribed manner`
  line `and the balance shall be applied to the payment of the arrears on account of which the sale was held and`
  line `the surplus, if any, shall be paid to the person whose property has been sold.`
obj_root_law_sections_77_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_78:
  sectionId (37903)
  sectionNo (78)
  orderNo 78
  title `Liability of certified purchaser.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_78_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37903&sectionno=78&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_78_content:
  string
  line `The person who has purchased any land and to whom a`
  line `certificate of purchase has been granted shall not be liable for the land revenue in respect of the land for`
  line `any period prior to the date of the sale.`
obj_root_law_sections_78_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_79:
  sectionId (37904)
  sectionNo (79)
  orderNo 79
  title `Precautionary measures in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_79_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37904&sectionno=79&orderno=79&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_79_content:
  string
  line `When the crop of any land or any portion of the`
  line `same is sold, mortgaged or otherwise disposed of, the Collector may, if he thinks it necessary, prevent its`
  line `being removed from the land until the demand for the current year in respect of the said land is paid`
  line `whether the date fixed for the payment of the same has arrived or not.`
obj_root_law_sections_79_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_80:
  sectionId (37905)
  sectionNo (80)
  orderNo 80
  title `Recovery of other public demands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_80_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37905&sectionno=80&orderno=80&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_80_content:
  string
  line `The following moneys may be recovered under this Act in`
  line `the same manner as an arrear of land revenue, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) rent, fees and royalties due to the Government for use or occupation of land or water or any`
  line `product of land;`
  line
  line `(b) all moneys falling due to the Government under any grant, lease or contract which provides`
  line `that they shall be re-coverable as arrears of land revenue;`
  line
  line `(c) all sums declared by this Act or any other law for the time being in force to be recoverable as`
  line `an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_80_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_81:
  sectionId (37906)
  sectionNo (81)
  orderNo 81
  title `Revenue officers to be courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_81_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37906&sectionno=81&orderno=81&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_81_content:
  string
  line `(1) A revenue officer, while exercising power under this Act or`
  line `any other law for the time being in force to inquire into or to decide any question arising for`
  line `determination between the Government and any person or between parties to any proceedings, shall be a`
  line `revenue court.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in this Act shall be deemed to limit or otherwise affect the inherent power of the revenue`
  line `court to make such orders as may be necessary for the ends of justice or to prevent the abuse of the`
  line `process of the revenue court.`
obj_root_law_sections_81_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_82:
  sectionId (37907)
  sectionNo (82)
  orderNo 82
  title `Place of hearing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_82_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37907&sectionno=82&orderno=82&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_82_content:
  string
  line `Except for reasons to be recorded in writing, no revenue officer shall inquire`
  line `into or hear any case at any place outside the local limits of his jurisdiction:`
  line
  line `Provided that a sub-divisional officer may inquire into or hear any case at the headquarters of the`
  line `district to which he is appointed.`
obj_root_law_sections_82_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_83:
  sectionId (37908)
  sectionNo (83)
  orderNo 83
  title `Power to enter upon and survey land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_83_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37908&sectionno=83&orderno=83&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_83_content:
  string
  line `All revenue officers and persons acting under their`
  line `orders may enter upon and survey any land and demarcate boundaries and do all other acts necessary for`
  line `the purpose of discharging their duties under this Act or any other law for the time being in force and in`
  line `so doing, shall cause no more damage than the circumstances of the case may require.`
obj_root_law_sections_83_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_84:
  sectionId (37909)
  sectionNo (84)
  orderNo 84
  title `Power to transfer cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_84_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37909&sectionno=84&orderno=84&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_84_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may transfer any case or class of cases arising`
  line `under this Act or any other law for the time being in force from any revenue officer to any other revenue`
  line `officer competent to deal with it.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector or a sub-divisional officer may transfer any case or class of cases arising under this`
  line `Act or any other law for the time being in force for inquiry or decision from his own file or from the file`
  line `of any revenue officer subordinate to him to the file of any other revenue officer subordinate to him`
  line `competent to deal with such case or class of cases.`
obj_root_law_sections_84_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_85:
  sectionId (38024)
  sectionNo (85)
  orderNo 85
  title `Power to take evidence, summon witnesses, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_85_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38024&sectionno=85&orderno=85&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_85_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every revenue officer not lower in rank`
  line `than a circle officer acting as a revenue court shall have power to take evidence and to summon any`
  line `person whose attendance he considers necessary, either as a party or as a witness or to produce any`
  line `document, for the purpose of any inquiry which such officer is legally empowered to make; and all`
  line `persons so summoned shall be bound to attend either in person or by an authorised agent as such officer`
  line `may direct, and to produce such documents as may be required.`
  line
  line `(2) Every summons shall be in writing, signed and sealed by the officer issuing it and shall be in such`
  line `form and be served in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_85_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_86:
  sectionId (38025)
  sectionNo (86)
  orderNo 86
  title `Compelling attendance of witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_86_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38025&sectionno=86&orderno=86&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_86_content:
  string
  line `If any person on whom a summons to attend as witness`
  line `or to produce any document has been served fails to comply with the summons, the officer by whom the`
  line `summons has been issued under section 85 may--`
  line
  line `(a) issue a bailable warrant of arrest;`
  line
  line `(b) order him to furnish security for appearance; or`
  line
  line `(c) impose upon him a fine not exceeding rupees twenty.`
obj_root_law_sections_86_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_87:
  sectionId (37911)
  sectionNo (87)
  orderNo 87
  title `Hearing in absence of party.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_87_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37911&sectionno=87&orderno=87&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_87_content:
  string
  line `(1) If, on the date fixed for hearing a case or proceeding, a`
  line `revenue officer finds that a summons or notice was not served on any party due to the failure of the`
  line `opposite party to pay the requisite process fees for such service, the case or proceeding may be dismissed`
  line `for default of payment of such process fees.`
  line
  line `(2) If any party to a case or proceeding before a revenue officer does not appear on the date fixed for`
  line `hearing, the case may be heard and determined in his absence or may be dismissed for default.`
  line
  line `(3) The party against whom any order is passed under sub-section (1) or (2) may apply, within thirty`
  line `days from the date of such order, to have it set aside on the ground that he was prevented by sufficient`
  line `cause from paying the requisite process fees or from appearing at the hearing; and the revenue officer`
  line `may, after notice to the opposite party and after making such inquiry as he considers necessary, set aside`
  line `the order passed.`
obj_root_law_sections_87_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_88:
  sectionId (37912)
  sectionNo (88)
  orderNo 88
  title `Adjournment of hearing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_88_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37912&sectionno=88&orderno=88&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_88_content:
  string
  line `(1) A revenue officer may, from time to time, for reasons to be`
  line `recorded, adjourn the hearing of a case or proceeding before him.`
  line `(2) The date and place of an adjourned hearing shall be intimated at the time of the adjournment to`
  line `such of the parties and witnesses as are present.`
obj_root_law_sections_88_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_89:
  sectionId (37913)
  sectionNo (89)
  orderNo 89
  title `Power to order payment of costs.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_89_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37913&sectionno=89&orderno=89&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_89_content:
  string
  line `A revenue officer may direct the parties to pay the cost`
  line `incurred in any case before him and also apportion the cost among the parties in such manner and to such`
  line `extent as he may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_89_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_90:
  sectionId (37914)
  sectionNo (90)
  orderNo 90
  title `Use of force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_90_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37914&sectionno=90&orderno=90&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_90_content:
  string
  line `Where any order is passed under this Act directing any person to deliver`
  line `possession of land or directing the eviction of any person from land, such order shall be executed by the`
  line `competent authority in such manner as may be prescribed and it shall be lawful for such authority, in`
  line `accordance with rules to be prescribed, to take such steps and use or cause to be used such force as may`
  line `be reasonably necessary for securing compliance with the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_90_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_91:
  sectionId (37915)
  sectionNo (91)
  orderNo 91
  title `Appearances before and applications to revenue officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_91_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37915&sectionno=91&orderno=91&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_91_content:
  string
  line `All appearances before,`
  line `applications to, and acts to be done before, any revenue officer under this Act or any other law for the`
  line `time being in force may be made or done by the parties themselves or by their authorised agents or by any`
  line `legal practitioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that any such appearance shall, if the revenue officer so directs, be made by the party in`
  line person.
obj_root_law_sections_91_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_92:
  sectionId (37916)
  sectionNo (92)
  orderNo 92
  title `Correction of error or omission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_92_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37916&sectionno=92&orderno=92&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_92_content:
  string
  line `Any revenue officer by whom an order was passed in a case`
  line `or proceeding may, either on his own motion or on the application of a party, correct any error or`
  line `omission not affecting a material part of the case or proceeding, after such notice to the parties as he may`
  line `consider necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_92_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_93:
  sectionId (37917)
  sectionNo (93)
  orderNo 93
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_93_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37917&sectionno=93&orderno=93&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_93_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise expressly provided, an appeal shall lie from every original order`
  line `passed under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) if such an order is passed by an officer subordinate to the sub-divisional officer, to the`
  line `sub-divisional officer;`
  line
  line `(b) if such an order is passed by the sub-divisional officer, to the Collector;`
  line
  line `(c) if such an order is passed by the Collector, to the Administrator;`
  line
  line `(d) if such an order is passed by an assistant survey and settlement officer, to the survey and`
  line `settlement officer or to a revenue officer notified by the Administrator in the Official Gazette to be`
  line `the appellate authority; and`
  line
  line `(e) if such an order is passed by a survey and settlement officer, to the director of settlement and`
  line `land records or to a revenue officer notified by the Administrator in the Official Gazette to be the`
  line `appellate authority.`
  line
  line `(2) A second appeal shall lie against any order passed In first appeal,--`
  line
  line `(a) if such an order is passed under clause (a) of sub-section (1) to the Collector;`
  line
  line `(b) if such an order is passed under clause (b) of sub-section (1), to the Administrator;`
  line
  line `(c) if such an order is passed under clause (d) of sub-section (1), to the director of settlement and`
  line `land records or to a revenue officer notified by the Administrator in the Official Gazette to be the`
  line `second appellate authority; and`
  line
  line `(d) If such an order is passed under clause (e) of sub-section (1), to the Administrator.`
obj_root_law_sections_93_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_94:
  sectionId (37918)
  sectionNo (94)
  orderNo 94
  title `Limitation of appeals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_94_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37918&sectionno=94&orderno=94&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_94_content:
  string
  line `(1) No appeal shall lie,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a first appeal, after the expiry of thirty days from the date of the order appealed`
  line `against; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a second appeal, after the expiry of sixty days from the date of the order`
  line `appealed against.`
  line
  line `(2) In computing the above periods, the time required to obtain copies of the order appealed against`
  line `shall be excluded.`
obj_root_law_sections_94_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_95:
  sectionId (37919)
  sectionNo (95)
  orderNo 95
  title Revision.
  content obj_root_law_sections_95_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37919&sectionno=95&orderno=95&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_95_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator or the Collector may, at any time, either on his own motion, or on`
  line `the application of any party, can for the records of any proceedings before any revenue officer`
  line `subordinate to him for the purpose of satisfying himself as to the legality or the propriety of any order`
  line `passed by such revenue officer, and may pass such order in reference thereto as he thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that he shall not vary or reverse any order affecting any right between private persons`
  line `without having given to the parties interested notice to appear and be heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_95_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_96:
  sectionId (37920)
  sectionNo (96)
  orderNo 96
  title `Review of orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_96_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37920&sectionno=96&orderno=96&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_96_content:
  string
  line `(1) A revenue officer may, either on his own motion or on the application of`
  line `any party interested, review any order passed by himself or by any of his predecessors-in-office and pass`
  line `such order in reference thereto as he thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that a revenue officer subordinate to the Collector shall, before reviewing any order under`
  line `this section, obtain the permission of the Collector and the Collector shall, before reviewing an order`
  line `passed by any of his predecessors-in-office obtain the permission of the Administrator.`
  line
  line `(2) No order affecting any question of right between private persons shall be reviewed except on the`
  line `application of a party to the proceedings or except after notice to the other party and no application for the`
  line `review of such order shall be entertained unless it is made within ninety days from the date of the order.`
  line
  line `(3) No order shall be reviewed except on the following grounds, namely:`
  line
  line `(i) discovery of new and important matter of evidence;`
  line
  line `(ii) some mistake or error apparent on the face of the record; or`
  line
  line `(iii) any other sufficient reason.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of this section, the Collector shall be deemed to be the successor-in-office of any`
  line `revenue officer who has left the district or who has ceased to exercise powers as a revenue officer and to`
  line `whom there is no successor in the district.`
  line
  line `(5) An order which has been dealt with in appeal or on revision shall not be reviewed by any officer`
  line `subordinate to the appellate or revisional authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_96_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_97:
  sectionId (37921)
  sectionNo (97)
  orderNo 97
  title `Stay of execution of orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_97_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37921&sectionno=97&orderno=97&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_97_content:
  string
  line `(1) A revenue officer who has passed any order or his`
  line `successor-in-office may, at any time before the expiry of the period prescribed for appeal, direct the stay`
  line `of execution of such order for such period as he thinks fit provided that no appeal has been filed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any authority before whom a case is pending in appeal or revision may direct the stay of`
  line `execution of the order appealed from or under revision for such period as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(3) The revenue officer or other authority directing such stay of execution of any order may impose`
  line `such conditions, or order such security to be furnished, as he or it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_97_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_98:
  sectionId (37922)
  sectionNo (98)
  orderNo 98
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_98_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37922&sectionno=98&orderno=98&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_98_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `rules for carrying out the purposes of this Part.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of appointment of revenue officers, survey officers and settlement officers, and`
  line `other village officers and servants, their powers and duties, the official seals, if any, to be used by`
  line `them and the size and description of the seals;`
  line
  line `(b) the Collector's powers of superintendence and control over other officers;`
  line
  line `(c) the officers who should hear and decide disputes regarding rights in or over any property`
  line `claimed by or against the Government and the procedure to be followed by them;`
  line
  line `(d) the disposal of Government lands by assignment or grant to individuals or to public purposes`
  line `and the terms and conditions subject to which such assignments or grants may be made;`
  line
  line `(e) the preservation and disposal of trees, brush, wood, jungle and other natural products on`
  line `Government land and the recovery of the value of trees or other natural product unauthorisedly`
  line `appropriated by persons;`
  line
  line `(f) the procedure for summary eviction of trespassers on Government land;`
  line
  line `(g) the alteration and revision of the land revenue in cases of alluvion or diluvion or of diversion`
  line `of land for purposes other than agriculture;`
  line
  line `(h) the grant of permission to use agricultural land for non- agricultural purposes;`
  line
  line `(i) the determination of additional rates for use of water;`
  line
  line `(j) the circumstances in which remission or suspension of revenue may be made and the rate of`
  line `such remission or suspension;`
  line
  line `(k) the form of receipt for payment of land revenue;`
  line
  line `(l) the conduct of surveys and settlements of land revenue;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of estimating the cost of cultivation and other expenses in relation to the inquiry`
  line `into profits of agriculture;`
  line
  line `(n) the division of survey numbers into sub-divisions and the assessment of sub-divisions;`
  line
  line `(o) the statistical, fiscal and other records and registers to be prepared and maintained under this`
  line Part;
  line
  line `(p) the manner in which the costs and expenses incidental to revenue survey or the construction,`
  line `repair and maintenance of boundary marks shall be determined and apportioned between persons who`
  line `are liable to bear the same;`
  line
  line `(q) the fixing, construction, laying out, maintenance and repair of boundary marks, and the`
  line `settlement of disputes relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(r) the division of areas into units for determining the revenue-rates and the preparation of the`
  line `table of revenue-rates;`
  line
  line `(s) the preparation and the preliminary and final publication of the record of rights and the table`
  line `of revenue-rates;`
  line
  line `(t) the hearing and disposal of objections to any entry or omission in the table of revenue-rates,`
  line `the record of rights, and the register of mutations;`
  line
  line `(u) the manner and extent of alteration or revision of revenue-rates during the term of settlement;`
  line
  line `(v) the correction of`
  line `bona fide errors and mistakes in the revenue records, registers and maps`
  line `prepared under this Part;`
  line
  line `(w) the manner in which the average yield of crops of land shall be ascertained;`
  line
  line `(x) the manner of holding inquiries by revenue officers under this Part;`
  line
  line `(y) the application of the provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), to cases`
  line `and proceedings before a revenue court;`
  line
  line `(z) the form of summons and other processes, notices, orders and proclamations to be issued or`
  line `made by revenue officers and the manner of their service;`
  line
  line `(aa) the procedure for the attachment and sale of property and the confirmation and the setting`
  line `aside of sales of immovable property under Chapter VII;`
  line
  line `(bb) the manner of publication of notices and proclamations of attachment and sale of property;`
  line
  line `(cc) the manner in which the cost and expenses incidental to the attachment and sale of property`
  line `shall be determined;`
  line
  line `(dd) the manner of payment of deposit and of the purchase money of property sold for arrears of`
  line `land revenue;`
  line
  line `(ee) the circumstances in which precautionary measures for securing the land revenue under`
  line `section 79 may be taken;`
  line
  line `(ff) the procedure for the transfer of cases from one revenue officer to another;`
  line
  line `(gg) the manner of preferring appeals or applications for revision or review, the documents to`
  line `accompany the memorandum of appeal or such application and the fee, if any, leviable therefor;`
  line
  line `(hh) the grant of certified copies and the payment of fees for inspection and grant of certified`
  line `copies of revenue records and registers;`
  line
  line `(ii) the mode of execution of any orders directing any person to deliver possession of land or to`
  line `be evicted from land, including the use of force for securing compliance with such order;`
  line
  line `(jj) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_98_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_99:
  sectionId (37923)
  sectionNo (99)
  orderNo 99
  title `Rights of raiyats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_99_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37923&sectionno=99&orderno=99&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_99_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that subject to the other`
  line `provisions of this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) the rights of a raiyat in his land shall be permanent, heritable and transferable;`
  line
  line `(b) the raiyat shall be entitled by himself, his servants, under-raiyats, agents or other`
  line `representatives to erect farm buildings, construct wells or tanks or make other improvements thereon`
  line `for the better cultivation of the land or its convenient or profitable use;`
  line
  line `(c) the raiyat is entitled to plant trees on his land, to enjoy the products thereof and to fell, utilise`
  line `or dispose of the timber of any trees on his land.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall entitle a raiyat to use his land to the detriment of any adjoining`
  line `land which is not his or in contravention of the provisions of any other law for the time being in force`
  line `applicable to such lands.`
obj_root_law_sections_99_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_100:
  sectionId (37924)
  sectionNo (100)
  orderNo 100
  title `Reservation of land for personal cultivation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_100_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37924&sectionno=100&orderno=100&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_100_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every raiyat who, at the commencement of`
  line `this Act, owns land in excess of a basic holding shall be entitled to apply to the competent authority for`
  line `the reservation for his personal cultivation of any parcel or parcels of his land leased to under-raiyats.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall be in the prescribed form and shall be made in the`
  line `prescribed manner within a period of one year from the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In the case of a person under disability, the application shall be made by his guardian`
  line `or his authorised agent, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_100_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_101:
  sectionId (37925)
  sectionNo (101)
  orderNo 101
  title `Procedure for reservation of lands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_101_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37925&sectionno=101&orderno=101&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_101_content:
  string
  line `(1) The competent authority shall, on an application`
  line `made under section 100, issue notice together with a copy of the application to each of the under-raiyats`
  line `holding land from the applicant requiring the under-raiyat to submit his objections, if any, within a period`
  line `of ninety days from the date of service of such notice or within such further period as the competent`
  line `authority may allow.`
  line
  line `(2) An under-raiyat on whom a notice has been served under sub-section (1), shall furnish to the`
  line `competent authority within the period aforesaid details of lands owned by him or held as under-raiyat of`
  line `any other raiyat and of lands which he selects for retention by him.`
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority shall, after considering the objections and the details, if any, furnished by`
  line `the under-raiyats and after making such inquiry as it may consider necessary, determine the land or lands,`
  line `not exceeding the permissible limit, which in its opinion having regard to all the circumstances of the case`
  line `may be reserved for personal cultivation of the raiyat and the lands which each of his under-raiyats may`
  line `be allowed to retain.`
obj_root_law_sections_101_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_102:
  sectionId (37926)
  sectionNo (102)
  orderNo 102
  title `“Permissible limit” defined.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_102_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37926&sectionno=102&orderno=102&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_102_content:
  string
  line `(1) In section 101, "permissible limit" means an area of land`
  line `which a raiyat may resume from under-raiyats for personal cultivation, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a person under disability, 25 standard acres;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of any other person who--`
  line
  line `(i) owns a basic holding or less, the entire area owned by him;`
  line
  line `(ii) owns more than a basic holding but not exceeding a family holding, one-half of the area`
  line `leased to under-raiyats or the area by which the land under his personal cultivation falls short of a`
  line `basic holding, whichever is greater;`
  line
  line `(iii) owns more than a family-holding,--`
  line
  line `(1) if he has no land, or any land which is less than a family holding, under his personal`
  line `cultivation, one-half of the area leased to under-raiyats but not exceeding the area by which`
  line `land under his personal cultivation falls short of a family holding, provided that the underraiyat is left with not less than a basic holding and provided further that a raiyat shall in any`
  line `case be entitled to resume an area by which land under his personal cultivation falls short of a`
  line `basic holding; and`
  line
  line `(2) if he has a family holding or more under his personal cultivation, the area leased to`
  line `under-raiyats but not exceeding the area by which land in his personal cultivation falls short`
  line `of 25 standard acres, provided that the under-raiyat is left with not less than a family holding.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purpose of determining the permissible limit of a raiyat under this`
  line `sub-section, any non-resumable land which he may hold as an under-raiyat shall also be taken into`
  line account.
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), an under-raiyat who under any law,`
  line `custom or usage is not liable to eviction at the commencement of this Act on the ground that the land is`
  line `required for personal cultivation, shall in all cases be left with a basic holding or the land actually held by`
  line `him, whichever is less.`
  line
  line `(3) Any transfer of land made on or after the 10th August, 1957 shall be disregarded in computing the`
  line `permissible limit.`
obj_root_law_sections_102_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_103:
  sectionId (37927)
  sectionNo (103)
  orderNo 103
  title `Land deemed to be reserved for personal cultivation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_103_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37927&sectionno=103&orderno=103&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_103_content:
  string
  line `In the case of a raiyat`
  line `who at the commencement of this Act does not own land in excess of a basic holding, all lands owned by`
  line `him and held by under-raiyats at such commencement shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 102, be deemed to have been reserved for his personal cultivation.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- Any transfer of land made on or after the 10th August, 1957 shall be disregarded in`
  line `determining the extent of land owned by a raiyat at the commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_103_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_104:
  sectionId (37928)
  sectionNo (104)
  orderNo 104
  title `Non-resumable land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_104_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37928&sectionno=104&orderno=104&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_104_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority shall declare every land which, under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 101, an under-raiyat is allowed to retain to be the non-resumable land of the`
  line under-raiyat.
obj_root_law_sections_104_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_105:
  sectionId (37929)
  sectionNo (105)
  orderNo 105
  title `Right to lease.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_105_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37929&sectionno=105&orderno=105&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_105_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, a raiyat may lease out his land to`
  line `another person on such rent not exceeding the maximum rent referred to in section 111 as may be agreed`
  line `upon between him and such person.`
  line
  line `(2) Every lease of land made after the commencement of this Act shall be for a period of five years`
  line `and at the end of the said period, and thereafter at the end of every such period of five years, the tenancy`
  line `shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), be deemed to be renewed for a further period of five`
  line `years on the same terms and conditions except to the extent that a modification thereof consistent with`
  line `this Act is agreed to by both parties.`
  line
  line `(3) In respect of any lease made after the commencement of this Act, a raiyat who is a member of the`
  line `Armed Forces of the Union, on his discharge from service or posting to the reserve, may by giving the`
  line `under-raiyat three months' notice in writing before the expiry of any year, and any other raiyat may by`
  line `giving the under-raiyat one year's notice in writing before the expiry of any term of five years, terminate`
  line `the tenancy if the raiyat requires the land bona fide for personal cultivation by him.`
obj_root_law_sections_105_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_106:
  sectionId (37930)
  sectionNo (106)
  orderNo 106
  title `Land left uncultivated.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_106_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37930&sectionno=106&orderno=106&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_106_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Collector is satisfied that any land has remained`
  line `uncultivated for a period of not less than two consecutive years otherwise than in accordance with rules`
  line `made in this behalf under this Act, and that it is necessary for the purpose of ensuring the full and`
  line `efficient use of the land for agriculture to do so, he may after making such inquiry as may be prescribed`
  line `lease out the land in accordance with the rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Any lease made under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to be a lease made by the raiyat under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 105.`
obj_root_law_sections_106_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_107:
  sectionId (37931)
  sectionNo (107)
  orderNo 107
  title Relinquishment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_107_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37931&sectionno=107&orderno=107&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_107_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any rules that may be made under this Act, a raiyat may`
  line `relinquish his rights in respect of any land in his possession in favour of Government by giving a notice in`
  line `writing to the competent authority in such form and manner as may be prescribed, not less than three`
  line `months before the close of any year and thereupon he shall cease to be a raiyat in respect of that land from`
  line `the year next following the date of notice:`
  line
  line `Provided that relinquishment of only a part of a holding or of a holding which, or part of which, is`
  line `subject to an encumbrance or a charge, shall not be valid.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person relinquishes his rights to a land under sub-section (1), the way to which lies through`
  line `other land retained by him, any future holder of the land relinquished shall be entitled to a right of way`
  line `through the land retained.`
obj_root_law_sections_107_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_108:
  sectionId (37932)
  sectionNo (108)
  orderNo 108
  title `Interest of under-raiyats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_108_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37932&sectionno=108&orderno=108&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_108_content:
  string
  line `(1) The interest of an under-raiyat in any land held by him as such`
  line `shall be heritable but, save as otherwise provided in this Act, shall not be transferable.`
  line
  line `(2) No under-raiyat shall be evicted from his land except as provided in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_108_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_109:
  sectionId (37933)
  sectionNo (109)
  orderNo 109
  title `Right to create a mortgage or charge.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_109_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37933&sectionno=109&orderno=109&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_109_content:
  string
  line `It shall be lawful for an under-raiyat to create a simple`
  line `mortgage or a charge on his interest in the land leased to him, in favour of the Government or a`
  line `co-operative society in consideration of any loan advanced to him by the Government or such society;`
  line `and in the event of his making default in the repayment of such loan in accordance with its terms, it shall`
  line `be lawful for the Government or the society, as the case may be, to cause his interest in the land to be`
  line `attached and sold and the proceeds applied in payment of such loan.`
obj_root_law_sections_109_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_110:
  sectionId (37934)
  sectionNo (110)
  orderNo 110
  title `Right to make improvements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_110_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37934&sectionno=110&orderno=110&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_110_content:
  string
  line `An under-raiyat may, with the permission in writing of the`
  line `raiyat, or if permission is refused without sufficient reason or is not given within two months, after`
  line `obtaining the orders of the competent authority in the prescribed manner, make at his own expense any`
  line `improvement to the land held by him, but shall not become liable to pay a higher rate of rent on account`
  line `of any increase of production or of any change in the nature of the crop raised, as a consequence of such`
  line improvement.
obj_root_law_sections_110_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_111:
  sectionId (37935)
  sectionNo (111)
  orderNo 111
  title `Maximum rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_111_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37935&sectionno=111&orderno=111&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_111_content:
  string
  line `The rent payable by an under-raiyat in respect of any land held by him shall`
  line `not exceed,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the rent is payable in kind as a share of the produce, one-fourth of the produce of such`
  line `land or its value estimated in the prescribed manner if plough cattle for the cultivation of such land is`
  line `supplied by the raiyat and one-fifth of such produce or its value as so estimated if plough cattle is not`
  line `supplied by the raiyat;`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, four times the land revenue payable in respect of the land.`
obj_root_law_sections_111_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_112:
  sectionId (37936)
  sectionNo (112)
  orderNo 112
  title `Payment of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_112_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37936&sectionno=112&orderno=112&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_112_content:
  string
  line `(1) The rent payable by an under-raiyat shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `section 111, be the rent agreed upon between him and the raiyat, or where there is no such agreement, the`
  line `reasonable rent.`
  line
  line `(2) The rent shall be paid at such times and in such manner as may have been agreed upon, or in the`
  line `absence of such agreement, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_112_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_113:
  sectionId (37937)
  sectionNo (113)
  orderNo 113
  title `Reasonable rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_113_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37937&sectionno=113&orderno=113&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_113_content:
  string
  line `(1) The competent authority may, on application made to it in this behalf by`
  line `the raiyat or the under-raiyat, determine the reasonable rent for any land.`
  line
  line `(2) The form of application under sub-section (1) and the procedure to be followed by the competent`
  line `authority shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) In determining the reasonable rent, the competent authority shall have regard to--`
  line
  line `(a) the rental value of lands used for similar purposes in the locality;`
  line
  line `(b) the profits of agriculture of similar lands in the locality;`
  line
  line `(c) the price of crops and commodities in the locality;`
  line
  line `(d) the improvements, if any, made to the land by the raiyat or the under-raiyat;`
  line
  line `(e) the land revenue payable in respect of the land; and`
  line
  line `(f) any other factor which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the reasonable rent for any land has been determined under this section, it shall not be`
  line `altered for a period of five years except on any of the following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the quality of the land has deteriorated by flood or other natural causes;`
  line
  line `(b) that there has been an increase in the produce of the land on account of improvements made to`
  line `it at the expense of the raiyat;`
  line
  line `(c) that the extent of land has been altered by more than one acre by alluvion or diluvion.`
  line
  line `(d) that the land has been partially or wholly rendered unfit for cultivation.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in sub-sections (1) to (4) shall affect the right of the Government to make an order`
  line `directing the determination of the reasonable rent of lands in any specified area.`
obj_root_law_sections_113_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_114:
  sectionId (37938)
  sectionNo (114)
  orderNo 114
  title `Commutation of rent payable in kind.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_114_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37938&sectionno=114&orderno=114&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_114_content:
  string
  line `(1) In any case in which rent is payable in kind, the`
  line `raiyat or the under-raiyat may apply in writing to the competent authority in the prescribed form and`
  line `manner, for commuting the rent into money rent.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of such application, the competent authority shall, after giving notice to the other party,`
  line `determine the money rent payable for the land in accordance with the following provisions but not`
  line `exceeding the maximum rent specified in section 111.`
  line
  line `(3) In determining the money rent, regard shall be had to--`
  line
  line `(a) the average money rent payable by under-raiyats for land of similar description and with`
  line `similar advantages in the vicinity;`
  line
  line `(b) the average value of the rent for the land actually received by the raiyat during the three years`
  line `preceding the date of application;`
  line
  line `(c) the average prices of crops and commodities in the locality during the three years preceding`
  line `the date of application;`
  line
  line `(d) the improvements, if any, made to the land by the raiyat or the under-raiyat; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other factor which may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_114_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_115:
  sectionId (37939)
  sectionNo (115)
  orderNo 115
  title `Receipt for payment of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_115_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37939&sectionno=115&orderno=115&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_115_content:
  string
  line `Every raiyat shall give or cause to be given a receipt for the rent`
  line `received by him or on his behalf in such form as may be prescribed duly signed by him or his authorised`
  line agent.
obj_root_law_sections_115_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_116:
  sectionId (37940)
  sectionNo (116)
  orderNo 116
  title `Refund of rent recovered in excess.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_116_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37940&sectionno=116&orderno=116&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_116_content:
  string
  line `If any raiyat recovers from an under-raiyat rent in excess`
  line `of the amount due under this Act, he shall forthwith refund the excess amount so recovered and shall also`
  line `be liable to punishment as provided in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_116_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_117:
  sectionId (37941)
  sectionNo (117)
  orderNo 117
  title `Suspension or remission of rent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_117_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37941&sectionno=117&orderno=117&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_117_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a raiyat has obtained from or been granted by the`
  line `Government any relief by way of suspension or remission, whether in whole or in part, of the land`
  line `revenue payable in respect of his land, he shall be bound to give, and the under-raiyat concerned shall be`
  line `entitled to receive from the raiyat, a corresponding or proportionate relief by way of suspension or`
  line `remission of rent payable in respect of such land.`
  line
  line `(2) The nature and extent of the relief which a raiyat is bound to give and which the under-raiyat is`
  line `entitled to receive under sub-section (1) shall be determined in accordance with the rules made under this`
  line Act.
  line
  line `(3) No suit shall lie and no decree of a civil court shall be executed for the recovery by a raiyat of any`
  line `rent the payment of which has been remitted, or during the period for which the payment of such rent has`
  line `been suspended, under this section.`
  line
  line `(4) The period during which the payment of rent is suspended under this section shall be excluded in`
  line `computing the period of limitation for any suit or proceeding for the recovery of such rent.`
  line
  line `(5) If any raiyat fails to suspend or remit the payment of rent as provided in sub-section (1), he shall`
  line `be liable to refund to the under-raiyat the amount recovered by him in contravention of the provisions of`
  line `this section and shall also be liable to punishment as provided in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_117_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_118:
  sectionId (37942)
  sectionNo (118)
  orderNo 118
  title `Eviction of under-raiyat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_118_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37942&sectionno=118&orderno=118&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_118_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall be evicted from any land held by him as`
  line `under-raiyat except under the order of the competent authority made on any of the following grounds,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the land has been reserved for personal cultivation of the raiyat under section 101, or is`
  line `deemed to have been reserved for personal cultivation of the raiyat under section 103;`
  line
  line `(b) that a notice has been given to the under-raiyat under sub-section (3) of section 105;`
  line
  line `(c) that the under-raiyat has intentionally and wilfully committed such acts of waste as are`
  line `calculated to impair materially or permanently the value or utility of the land for agricultural`
  line purposes;
  line
  line `(d) that the under-raiyat has failed to pay rent within a period of three months after it falls due:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority may, if it thinks fit, grant further time not exceeding six`
  line `months for payment of the rent;`
  line
  line `(e) that the under-raiyat, not being a person under disability, has, after the commencement of this`
  line `Act, sublet the land without the consent in writing of the raiyat.`
  line
  line `(2) No order for eviction of an under-raiyat shall be executed till the standing crops, if any, on the`
  line `land are harvested.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any land has been reserved for the personal cultivation of a raiyat by an order made under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 101, no suit or application for the eviction of the under-raiyat in respect of such`
  line `land under clause (a) of sub-section (1) shall lie after the expiry of five years from the commencement of`
  line `this Act or one year from the date of the said order, whichever is later:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such raiyat is a person under disability, such suit or application may be`
  line `instituted or made within a period of five years from the date when the disability ceases.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the disability of a person shall cease,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a widow, if she re-marries, on the date of her remarriage or if any person`
  line `succeeds to the widow on her death, on the date of her death;`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a minor, on the date of his attaining majority;`
  line
  line `(c) in the case of a woman who is unmarried or who is divorced or judicially separated from her`
  line `husband on the date of her marriage or remarriage, as the case may be, or in the case of a woman`
  line `whose husband is a person falling under clause (d) or (e), on the date on which the disability of the`
  line `husband ceases;`
  line
  line `(d) in the case of a person who is a member of the Armed Forces of the Union, on the date of his`
  line `discharge from service or of his posting to the reserve;`
  line
  line `(e) in the case of a person suffering from a physical or mental disability, on the date on which the`
  line `disability ceases to exist.`
obj_root_law_sections_118_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_119:
  sectionId (37943)
  sectionNo (119)
  orderNo 119
  title `Restoration of possession of land to under-raiyat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_119_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37943&sectionno=119&orderno=119&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_119_content:
  string
  line `Where a person who has taken possession`
  line `of any land by evicting an under-raiyat therefrom on the ground that the land had been reserved for`
  line `personal cultivation by him, fails to cultivate such land personally within one year from the date on which`
  line `he took possession thereof or ceases to cultivate such land personally in any year during a period of four`
  line `years next following, the under-raiyat shall be entitled to be restored to possession of the land from which`
  line `he was evicted.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section, land shall not be deemed to be under the personal`
  line `cultivation of a person (not being a person under disability) unless such person or a member of his family`
  line `engages himself in the principal agricultural operations.`
obj_root_law_sections_119_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_120:
  sectionId (37944)
  sectionNo (120)
  orderNo 120
  title `Certain lands to be non-resumable land of under-raiyat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_120_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37944&sectionno=120&orderno=120&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_120_content:
  string
  line `If a raiyat fails to`
  line
  line `(a) apply for reservation of any land within the period prescribed in section 100, and the land is`
  line `not deemed to have been reserved under section 103, or`
  line
  line `(b) file a suit or application for the eviction of the under-raiyat from any land reserved under`
  line `section 101 within the period prescribed in sub-section (3) of section 118, or`
  line
  line `(c) cultivate or ceases to cultivate the land and the under-raiyat is restored to possession of the`
  line `land under section 119,`
  line
  line `the competent authority may suo motu and shall, on application, after making such inquiry as may be`
  line `prescribed, declare the land to be the non-resumable land of the under-raiyat.`
obj_root_law_sections_120_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_121:
  sectionId (37945)
  sectionNo (121)
  orderNo 121
  title `Compensation for improvements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_121_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37945&sectionno=121&orderno=121&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_121_content:
  string
  line `(1) An under-raiyat who has made any improvement at his`
  line `own expense on the land leased to him shall, if he is to be evicted under the provisions of this Chapter, be`
  line `entitled to receive compensation, before he is so evicted, for such improvement as, in the opinion of the`
  line `competent authority, is reasonable.`
  line
  line `(2) The compensation payable to an under-raiyat under sub-section (1) shall be determined in`
  line `accordance with the value of such improvements on the date of eviction, and in determining such`
  line `compensation, regard shall be had to the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount by which the value of the land has increased by reason of the improvement;`
  line
  line `(b) the condition of the improvement at the date of the determination of the value thereof and the`
  line `probable duration of its effect;`
  line
  line `(c) the labour and capital involved in the making of the improvement; and`
  line
  line `(d) the advantages secured by the under-raiyat in consideration of the improvement made by him.`
  line
  line `(3) In any case in which compensation is payable to an under-raiyat under this section, the competent`
  line `authority may direct that--`
  line
  line `(a) the whole or any part of any loan which the under-raiyat has taken on the security of his`
  line `interest in the land under section 109 and which is outstanding shall be deducted from such`
  line `compensation and paid to the Government or the co-operative society, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) any arrear of rent due by the under-raiyat to the raiyat and the costs, if any, awarded to the`
  line `raiyat shall be adjusted against the compensation.`
obj_root_law_sections_121_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_122:
  sectionId (37946)
  sectionNo (122)
  orderNo 122
  title `Under-raiyat may remove building, works, etc., not deemed improvements.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_122_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37946&sectionno=122&orderno=122&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_122_content:
  string
  line An
  line `under-raiyat against whom an order of eviction has been passed, shall be entitled to remove within such`
  line `time as is deemed reasonable by the competent authority any work of improvement which can be severed`
  line `from the land and which the under-raiyat desires to remove, or any building or construction or work`
  line `(which is not an improvement) in respect of which the raiyat is not willing to pay the compensation.`
obj_root_law_sections_122_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_123:
  sectionId (37947)
  sectionNo (123)
  orderNo 123
  title `Restoration of possession of land in certain other cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_123_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37947&sectionno=123&orderno=123&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_123_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an under-raiyat of any`
  line `land has, on or after the 10th August, 1957, surrendered, or been evicted from, such land and the`
  line `surrender or eviction could not have taken place if this Act had been in force on the date of such surrender`
  line `or eviction, the competent authority may, suo motu or on application made by the under-raiyat, restore`
  line `him to possession of the land which he surrendered or from which he was evicted unless some other`
  line `under-raiyat, not being a member of the raiyats family, had bona fide been admitted to possession of`
  line `such land.`
  line
  line `(2) The competent authority shall, before making an order under sub-section (1), make such inquiry`
  line `as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_123_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_124:
  sectionId (37948)
  sectionNo (124)
  orderNo 124
  title `Relief against termination of tenancy for act of waste.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_124_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37948&sectionno=124&orderno=124&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_124_content:
  string
  line `Where a tenancy is sought to be`
  line `terminated on the ground that the under-raiyat has materially impaired the value or utility of the land for`
  line `agricultural purposes, if the damage to the land admits of being repaired or if pecuniary compensation`
  line `would afford adequate relief, no proceeding for eviction shall lie against the under-raiyat unless and until`
  line `the raiyat has served on the under-raiyat a notice in writing specifying the damage complained of and the`
  line `under-raiyat has failed within a period of one year from the service of such notice to repair the damage or`
  line `to pay compensation therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_124_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_125:
  sectionId (37949)
  sectionNo (125)
  orderNo 125
  title `Surrender of land by under-raiyat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_125_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37949&sectionno=125&orderno=125&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_125_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the commencement of this Act, no under-raiyat`
  line `shall surrender any land held by him as such, and no raiyat shall enter upon the land surrendered by the`
  line `under-raiyat, without the previous permission in writing of the competent authority.`
  line
  line `(2) Such permission shall be granted if, after making such inquiry as may be prescribed, the`
  line `competent authority is satisfied that the proposed surrender is bona fide and in case the surrender is by a`
  line `person who was holding the land as under-raiyat immediately before the commencement of this Act, the`
  line `permissible limit of the raiyat concerned is not exceeded by such surrender; in other cases, the permission`
  line `shall be refused.`
  line
  line `(3) Where permission is refused in any case, and the under-raiyat gives a declaration in writing`
  line `relinquishing his rights in the land, the competent authority shall, in accordance with the rules made in`
  line `this behalf, lease out the land to any other person who shall acquire all the rights of the under-raiyat who`
  line `relinquished his rights.`
obj_root_law_sections_125_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_126:
  sectionId (37950)
  sectionNo (126)
  orderNo 126
  title `Transfer of ownership of land to under-raiyats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_126_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37950&sectionno=126&orderno=126&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_126_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the other provisions of this Act,`
  line `the ownership of any land which is declared to be the non-resumable land of an under-raiyat under`
  line `section 104 or section 120 shall stand transferred from the raiyat thereof to the under-raiyat with effect`
  line `from the date of such declaration, and the under-raiyat shall become the owner of such land and be liable`
  line `to pay land revenue therefor.`
obj_root_law_sections_126_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_127:
  sectionId (37951)
  sectionNo (127)
  orderNo 127
  title `Compensation to raiyat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_127_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37951&sectionno=127&orderno=127&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_127_content:
  string
  line `(1) In respect of every land the ownership of which stands`
  line `transferred to the under-raiyat under section 126, the raiyat shall be entitled to compensation which shall`
  line `consist of the aggregate of the following amounts, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) an amount equal to thirty times the full land revenue payable for the land or, if the land is held`
  line `revenue-free or at a concessional rate, thirty times the amount of land revenue payable for similar`
  line `lands in the locality;`
  line
  line `(b) the value of trees, if any, planted by the raiyat.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where any improvement has been made on the land at the expense of the raiyat at any`
  line `time subsequent to the last settlement, the land revenue for the purpose of this section shall be the land`
  line `revenue payable for similar lands in the locality.`
  line
  line `(2) The land revenue payable for similar lands in the locality and the value of trees referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be determined in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(3) Every raiyat entitled to compensation under this section shall, within a period of six months from`
  line `the date of the declaration referred to in section 126, apply to the competent authority in the prescribed`
  line `manner for determining the compensation.`
obj_root_law_sections_127_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_128:
  sectionId (37952)
  sectionNo (128)
  orderNo 128
  title `Payment of compensation to raiyat.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_128_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37952&sectionno=128&orderno=128&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_128_content:
  string
  line `(1) The compensation to which a raiyat is entitled under`
  line `section 127 shall be paid to him by the Government in the first instance, and it may be paid in cash, in`
  line `lump sum or in annual instalments not exceeding twenty or in the form of bonds which may be negotiable`
  line `or non-negotiable but transferable.`
  line
  line `(2) From the date of the declaration referred to in section 126, the raiyat shall be entitled to interest at`
  line `the rate of 2� per cent. per annum on the compensation or such portion thereof as remains un paid.`
  line
  line `(3) Any mortgage of, or encumbrance on, the land of which the ownership is transferred to the`
  line `under-raiyat under section 126 shall be a valid charge on the amount of compensation payable to the`
  line raiyat.
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) to (3), where the person entitled to`
  line `compensation under section 127 is a charitable or religious institution, the compensation shall, instead of`
  line `being assessed under that section, be assessed as a perpetual annuity equal to the reasonable rent for the`
  line `land, less the land revenue payable on such land. The amount so assessed shall be paid to such institution`
  line `in the prescribed manner.`
obj_root_law_sections_128_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_129:
  sectionId (37953)
  sectionNo (129)
  orderNo 129
  title `Under-raiyat to pay compensation amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_129_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37953&sectionno=129&orderno=129&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_129_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every under-raiyat to whom ownership of`
  line `any land has been transferred under section 126 shall be liable to pay to the Government in respect of that`
  line `land compensation as determined under section 127.`
  line
  line `(2) The compensation shall be payable in cash, in lump sum or in such number of annual instalments,`
  line `not exceeding twenty as may prescribed. Interest at the rate of 2^1/2 per cent. per annum shall be payable on`
  line `the compensation or such portion thereof as remains unpaid.`
  line
  line `(3) The compensation payable under this section shall be a charge on the land.`
  line
  line `(4) The compensation or any instalment thereof shall be re-coverable in the same manner as an arrear`
  line `of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_129_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_130:
  sectionId (37954)
  sectionNo (130)
  orderNo 130
  title `Issue of certificate to under-raiyats.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_130_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37954&sectionno=130&orderno=130&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_130_content:
  string
  line `When the compensation or the first instalment of the`
  line `compensation, as the case may be, has been paid by the under-raiyat, the competent authority may`
  line `suo motu and shall, on application made to it in this behalf, issue to the under-raiyat a certificate in the`
  line `prescribed form declaring him to be the owner of the land specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_130_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_131:
  sectionId (37955)
  sectionNo (131)
  orderNo 131
  title `First option to purchase.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_131_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37955&sectionno=131&orderno=131&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_131_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a raiyat at any time intends to sell his land held by an`
  line `under-raiyat, he shall give notice in writing of his intention to such under-raiyat and offer to sell the land`
  line `to him. In case the latter intends to purchase the land, he shall intimate in writing his readiness to do so`
  line `within two months from the date of receipt of such notice.`
  line
  line `(2) If there is any dispute about the reasonable price payable for the land, either the raiyat or the`
  line `under-raiyat may apply in writing to the competent authority for determining the reasonable price; and the`
  line `competent authority, after giving notice to the other party and to all other persons interested in the land`
  line `and after making such inquiry as it thinks fit, shall fix the reasonable price of the land which shall be the`
  line `average of the prices obtaining for similar lands in the locality during the ten years immediately preceding`
  line `the date on which the application is made.`
  line
  line `(3) The under-raiyat shall deposit with the competent authority the amount of the price determined`
  line `under sub-section (2) within such period as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) On deposit of the entire amount of the reasonable price, the competent authority shall issue a`
  line `certificate in the prescribed form to the under-raiyat declaring him to be the purchaser of the land; the`
  line `competent authority shall also direct that the reasonable price deposited shall be paid to the raiyat.`
  line
  line `(5) If an under-raiyat does not exercise the right of purchase in response to the notice given to him by`
  line `the raiyat under sub-section (1) or fails to deposit the amount of the price as required by sub-section (3),`
  line `such under-raiyat shall forfeit his right of purchase, and the raiyat shall be entitled to sell such land to any`
  line `other person.`
  line
  line `(6) The forfeiture of the right to purchase any land under this section shall not affect the other rights`
  line `of the under-raiyat in such land.`
obj_root_law_sections_131_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_132:
  sectionId (37956)
  sectionNo (132)
  orderNo 132
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_132_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37956&sectionno=132&orderno=132&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_132_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Part.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the form of notices to be issued under this Part and the manner of their service;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of holding inquiries under this Part;`
  line
  line `(c) the circumstances in which and the period for which land used for agricultural purposes may`
  line `be left uncultivated;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions subject to which lands may be leased by the Collector under section 106;`
  line
  line `(e) the form of applications to be made under this Part, the authorities to whom they may be made`
  line `and the procedure to be followed by such authorities in disposing of the applications;`
  line
  line `(f) the determination of the value of the produce of land, the profits of agriculture, and the rental`
  line `values of land, for the purposes of this Part;`
  line
  line `(g) the time and manner of payment of rent by the under-raiyat;`
  line
  line `(h) the form of receipt for rent to be given by the raiyat;`
  line
  line `(i) the factors to be taken into account in determining reasonable rent for land and in commuting`
  line `rent in kind into money rent;`
  line
  line `(j) the nature and the extent of relief to the under-raiyat in cases of suspension or remission of`
  line `land revenue by the Government;`
  line
  line `(k) the determination of compensation for improvements to under-raiyats who are evicted from`
  line land;
  line
  line `(l) the grant of permission to surrender land;`
  line
  line `(m) the determination of the amount of compensation payable to the raiyat in respect of the`
  line `non-resumable lands of under-raiyats;`
  line
  line `(n) the form of certificates to be granted to under-raiyats;`
  line
  line `(o) the determination of the price to be paid by under-raiyat for land in respect of which the first`
  line `option to purchase is exercised;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_132_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_133:
  sectionId (37957)
  sectionNo (133)
  orderNo 133
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_133_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37957&sectionno=133&orderno=133&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_133_content:
  string
  line `In this Part,--`
  line
  line `(a) "estate" means lands included under one entry in any of the general registers of`
  line `revenue-paying and revenue-free lands and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) revenue-free lands not entered in any register, and`
  line
  line `(ii) a part of, or a share in, an estate;`
  line
  line `(b) "homestead" means a dwelling house together with any courtyard, compound, garden, or`
  line `outhouse and includes any outbuildings used for purposes connected with agriculture and any family`
  line `graveyard, library, office, guest house, grainstore, latrines, boundary walls, tanks, wells or places of`
  line `worship appertaining to such dwelling house;`
  line
  line `(c) "intermediary" means a person who holds in an estate the right, title or interest of a talukdar`
  line `and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a person who holds land either revenue-free or at a concessional rate, and`
  line
  line `(ii) a tenure holder;`
  line
  line `(d) "tenant" means a person who cultivates or holds the land of an intermediary under an`
  line `agreement, express or implied, on condition of paying therefor rent in cash or in kind or delivering a`
  line `share of the produce and includes a person who cultivates or holds land of an intermediary under the`
  line `system generally known as "bhag", "adhi" or "barga"; and the term "sub-tenant" shall be construed`
  line accordingly;
  line
  line `(e) "tenure holder" means a person who has acquired from an intermediary the right to hold lands`
  line `for the purpose of collecting rents or bringing them under cultivation by establishIng tenants thereon.`
obj_root_law_sections_133_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_134:
  sectionId (37958)
  sectionNo (134)
  orderNo 134
  title `Notification vesting estates in the State.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_134_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37958&sectionno=134&orderno=134&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_134_content:
  string
  line `(1) As soon as may be after the commencement of`
  line `this Act, the Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that, with effect from the`
  line `date specified in the notification (hereinafter referred to as the vesting date), all estates situated in any`
  line `area or areas and all rights, title and interest of every intermediary in such estates shall vest in the`
  line `Government free from all encumbrances.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under sub-section (1) shall also be published in such other manner as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) The publication of a notification in the manner provided in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall be`
  line `conclusive evidence of the notice of declaration to the intermediaries whose interests are affected by such`
  line notification
obj_root_law_sections_134_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_135:
  sectionId (37959)
  sectionNo (135)
  orderNo 135
  title `Consequences of notification under section 134.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_135_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37959&sectionno=135&orderno=135&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_135_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any`
  line `law for the time being in force or in any agreement or contract, express or implied, with effect from the`
  line `vesting date,--`
  line
  line `(a) each estate to which the notification relates and all rights, title and interest of intermediaries in`
  line `such estate shall vest in the Government free from all encumbrances, including--`
  line
  line `(i) rights in hats, bazars, ferries, forests, wastelands, abadi sites, fisheries, tolls and other`
  line interests;
  line
  line `(ii) rights in any building other than a dwelling house or in any part of such building, used`
  line `primarily as office cutcherry for collection of rent;`
  line
  line `(b) all grants and confirmation of title to the estate and rights therein made in favour of an`
  line `intermediary shall cease and determine;`
  line
  line `(c) any building used for educational or charitable purposes and held by the intermediary shall`
  line `vest in the Government for those educational or charitable purposes;`
  line
  line `(d) subject to the other provisions of this Act, every tenant holding any land under an`
  line `intermediary shall hold the same directly under the Government as a raiyat thereof and shall be liable`
  line `to pay to the Government land revenue equal to the rent payable by him to the intermediary on the`
  line `vesting date, subject to a maximum of the value of one-eighth of the gross produce which value shall`
  line `be determined in the manner prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the tenant shall become the owner of any building or structure constructed on such`
  line `land at the expense of the intermediary on payment of such compensation to the intermediary as is`
  line `equivalent to its market value on the vesting date, which value shall be determined in accordance with`
  line `the rules made in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(e) all arrears of land revenue, local rates, cesses and other dues lawfully payable to the`
  line `Government by the intermediary on the vesting date in respect of the estate shall, without prejudice to`
  line `any other mode of recovery, be recoverable by deduction from the compensation payable to the`
  line intermediary;
  line
  line `(f) all rents and other dues in respect of the estate for any period after the vesting date which, but`
  line `for this Act, would be payable to an intermediary shall be payable to the Government and any`
  line `payment made in contravention of this clause shall not be valid discharge of the person liable to pay`
  line `the same;`
  line
  line `(g) where under any agreement or contract made before the vesting date, any rent, cess, local rate`
  line `or other dues for any period after the said date has been paid to or compounded of released by an`
  line `intermediary, the same shall, notwithstanding such agreement or contract, be recoverable by the`
  line `Government from the intermediary, and may, without prejudice to any other mode of recovery, be`
  line `realised by deduction from the compensation payable to the intermediary.`
obj_root_law_sections_135_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_136:
  sectionId (37960)
  sectionNo (136)
  orderNo 136
  title `Rights of intermediary to certain lands.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_136_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37960&sectionno=136&orderno=136&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_136_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections`
  line `134 and 135, an intermediary shall, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), be entitled to retain with`
  line `effect from the vesting date,--`
  line
  line `(a) homesteads, buildings and structures together with the lands appurtenant thereto in the`
  line `occupation of the intermediary other than buildings vested in the Government under section 135;`
  line
  line `(b) lands under the personal cultivation of the intermediary;`
  line
  line `(c) lands in which permanent rights have not already accrued to a tenant under any custom,`
  line `agreement or law and which have been leased by an intermediary who, both at the commencement of`
  line `the lease and on the vesting date, was a person under disability;`
  line
  line `(d) lands held by the intermediary as mortgagor which are subject to usufructuary mortgage and`
  line `are under the personal cultivation of the mortgagee;`
  line
  line `(e) lands comprised in orchards or used for the purpose of live-stock breeding, poultry farming, or`
  line `dairy farming, which are in the occupation of the intermediary;`
  line
  line `(f) so much of the lands comprised in a tea garden, mill, factory or workshop as in the opinion of`
  line `the Administrator is required for such tea garden, mill, factory or workshop.`
  line
  line `(2) An intermediary who is entitled to retain possession of any land under sub-section (1) shall hold`
  line `such land directly under the Government from the vesting date as a raiyat thereof and be liable to pay`
  line `therefor land revenue at full rate applicable to similar lands in the locality.`
obj_root_law_sections_136_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_137:
  sectionId (37961)
  sectionNo (137)
  orderNo 137
  title `Collector to take charge of estates, etc., vested in the Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_137_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37961&sectionno=137&orderno=137&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_137_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Collector shall`
  line `take charge of estates and interests of intermediaries which vest in the Government under section 135.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose aforesaid, the Collector may, by written order served in the prescribed manner,`
  line `require any intermediary or other person in possession, of any such estate or interest to give up such`
  line `possession by a date to be specified in the order (which shall not be earlier than sixty days from the date`
  line `of service of the order) or to deliver by that date any documents, registers, or records, connected with the`
  line `management of such estate or interest which are in his custody or to furnish a statement in the prescribed`
  line `form in respect of such estate or interest.`
  line
  line `(3) The Collector or any other officer authorised by him in this behalf may take such steps or use such`
  line `force as may be necessary to enforce compliance with the order and may also enter any building or place`
  line `for the purpose of taking possession of the documents, registers or records referred to in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) An intermediary shall be entitled to make inspection of any documents, registers or records which`
  line `have been delivered to or taken possession of by the Collector, to make notes therefrom or to have`
  line `certified copies thereof granted to him. No fees shall be charged for making inspection or for making`
  line `notes, but fees may be charged, according to the prescribed scale, for the grant of certified copies.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall be deemed to authorise the collector to take possession of--`
  line
  line `(a) any land or of any right of an intermediary therein, which may be retained by the intermediary`
  line `under section 136, or`
  line
  line `(b) any religious institution or any building connected therewith.`
obj_root_law_sections_137_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_138:
  sectionId (37962)
  sectionNo (138)
  orderNo 138
  title `Decision of disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_138_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37962&sectionno=138&orderno=138&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_138_content:
  string
  line `If there is any dispute as to the possession of any homestead or land or`
  line `building referred to in sub-section (1) of section 136, the Collector shall, on application made to him in`
  line `this behalf, make such inquiry as he deems fit and pass such orders thereon as may appear to him just and`
  line proper.
obj_root_law_sections_138_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_139:
  sectionId (37963)
  sectionNo (139)
  orderNo 139
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_139_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37963&sectionno=139&orderno=139&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_139_content:
  string
  line `An appeal against an order of the Collector passed under section 138, if preferred`
  line `within sixty days of such order, shall lie to the District Judge having jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_139_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_140:
  sectionId (37964)
  sectionNo (140)
  orderNo 140
  title `Intermediaries entitled to receive compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_140_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37964&sectionno=140&orderno=140&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_140_content:
  string
  line `Every intermediary, whose right, title and`
  line `interest in any estate vest in the Government under Chapter XI shall be entitled to receive and be paid`
  line `therefor compensation as hereinafter provided.`
obj_root_law_sections_140_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_141:
  sectionId (37965)
  sectionNo (141)
  orderNo 141
  title `Date from which compensation shall be due.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_141_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37965&sectionno=141&orderno=141&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_141_content:
  string
  line `The compensation referred to in section 140`
  line `shall be due as from the vesting date and the portion remaining unpaid shall carry interest at the rate of`
  line 2
  line `1/2 per cent. per annum`
obj_root_law_sections_141_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_142:
  sectionId (37966)
  sectionNo (142)
  orderNo 142
  title `Every intermediary to be treated as a separate unit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_142_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37966&sectionno=142&orderno=142&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_142_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of assessing`
  line `compensation under this Chapter,--`
  line
  line `(a) every intermediary shall be treated as a separate unit;`
  line
  line `(b) if two or more intermediaries hold an estate or any interest therein jointly, the share of each`
  line `intermediary in such estate or interest shall be treated as a separate unit:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such estate or interest is held by a Hindu joint family consisting of a`
  line `common ancestor in the male line and his descendants, the family shall if the common ancestor was`
  line `alive on the vesting date, be treated as one unit;`
  line
  line `(c) if an intermediary holds shares or interest in two or more estates, the aggregate of his shares or`
  line `interest in all such estates shall be treated as a single unit.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law, no partition or transfer by`
  line `way of sale or gift of an estate or part thereof made on or after the 10th August, 1957, shall be recognised`
  line `for the purpose of assessing the compensation.`
  line
  line `(3) Nothing in sub-section (2) shall apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) any sale made under an order of court in execution of any decree or order for payment of`
  line `money, or`
  line
  line `(b) any sale or gift made in favour of a wakf, a trust, an endowment or a society registered under`
  line `the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) and established wholly for charitable purposes,`
  line `unless the Government in any particular case directs otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_142_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_143:
  sectionId (37967)
  sectionNo (143)
  orderNo 143
  title `Appointment of compensation officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_143_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37967&sectionno=143&orderno=143&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_143_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator shall, as soon as possible after the`
  line `publication of a notification under section 134, appoint one or more officers to be compensation officers`
  line `to prepare compensation assessment rolls and to perform such other duties as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_143_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_144:
  sectionId (37968)
  sectionNo (144)
  orderNo 144
  title `Compensation assessment roll.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_144_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37968&sectionno=144&orderno=144&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_144_content:
  string
  line `(1) The compensation officer shall prepare a compensation`
  line `assessment roll in respect of every estate vested in the Government under Chapter XI.`
  line
  line `(2) The compensation assessment roll shall contain particulars of the gross income and the net income`
  line `from the estate, the share of the net income of the intermediary or each of the intermediaries, the amount`
  line `of compensation payable to him or them and such other particulars as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where an intermediary has shares or interest in two or more estates all of which have vested in the`
  line `Government, the particulars of the shares or interest of such intermediary in the net income from all such`
  line `estates and the compensation payable to him in respect of his shares or interest in all such estates shall be`
  line `shown in the compensation assessment roll relating to any one of such estates.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an intermediary has shares or interest in two or more estates either or any of which has not`
  line `vested in the Government, the compensation payable to the intermediary shall be determined after all`
  line `such estates have vested in the Government, on the basis of the aggregate of his shares or interest in the`
  line `net income from all such estates.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in sub-section (4) shall be construed as authorising the postponement of payment of ad`
  line `interim compensation to any such intermediary as is referred to in that sub-section in respect of the estate`
  line `or estates which have vested in the Government.`
  line
  line `(6) For the purpose of preparing the compensation assessment roll, the compensation officer may`
  line `require an intermediary to submit such statements and furnish such particulars as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_144_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_145:
  sectionId (37969)
  sectionNo (145)
  orderNo 145
  title `Determination of gross income and net income.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_145_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37969&sectionno=145&orderno=145&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_145_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of assessment of`
  line `compensation payable in respect of an estate,--`
  line
  line `(a) the gross income from the estate shall be taken to consist of--`
  line
  line `(i) in respect of lands other than those referred to in section 136, the rents, cesses, local rates`
  line `and other amounts payable or deemed to be payable to the intermediary or intermediaries by the`
  line `tenants and tenure-holders for the previous year, including the commuted value of rents payable`
  line `in kind which value shall be determined in the prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(ii) the gross income from abadi sites, fisheries, hats, bazars, ferries, forests, tolls, waste`
  line `lands and other interests in the estate for the previous year;`
  line
  line `(iii) the aggregate of the annual rents for the previous year from buildings used as offices or`
  line `cutcherries and any other building which vest in the Government;`
  line
  line `(iv) any other income during the previous year appertaining to the estate vesting in the`
  line `Government not expressly mentioned in the foregoing sub-clauses;`
  line
  line `(b) the net income from the estate shall be computed by deducting from the gross income the`
  line `following, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) any sum which was payable by the intermediary or intermediaries during the previous year`
  line `as land revenue, cesses, local rates or rent to the Government in respect of the interests to which`
  line `the gross income relates;`
  line
  line `(ii) any sum payable under the Bengal Agricultural Income-tax Act 1944 (Ben. IV of 1944),`
  line `as extended to Tripura or the Indian Income-tax Act 1922 (11 of 1922), during the previous year`
  line `as defined in those Acts, in respect of the interests to which the gross income relates;`
  line
  line `(iii) charges on account of management and collection at the following rates, namely:--`
  line
  line `Amount of gross income Rate`
  line
  line `(a) Where the gross income exceeds Rs. 30,000. 15 per centum of such gross income.`
  line
  line `(b) Where the gross income exceeds Rs. 10,000 12^1/2per centum of such gross income.`
  line `but does not exceed Rs. 30,000.`
  line
  line `(c) Where the gross income exceeds Rs. 5,000 10 per centum of such gross income.`
  line `but does not exceed Rs. 10,000.`
  line
  line `(d) Where the gross income exceeds Rs. 2,500 7^1/2 per centum of such gross income.`
  line `but does not exceed Rs. 5,000.`
  line
  line `(e) Where the gross income does not exceed 5 per centum of such gross income.`
  line `Rs. 2,500.`
  line
  line `Provided that the net income (after deducting the charges on account of management and collection)`
  line `from an estate which falls under item (a), (b), (c) or (d) shall in no case be less than the maximum net`
  line `income from an estate which falls under the item immediately, following.`
  line
  line `Illustration.-- The net income after deducting the charges on account of management and collection`
  line `at 121/2 per cent. under item (b) from an estate the gross income of which is Rs. 10,100 will be`
  line `Rs. 8,837.50 while the net income after deducting the charges on account of management at 10 per cent.`
  line `under item (c) from an estate the gross income of which is Rs.10,000 will be Rs. 9,000; under the proviso,`
  line `the net income from the first mentioned estate shall be taken to be Rs. 9,000 and not Rs. 8,837.50.`
  line
  line `(2) The net income from the estate as determined under sub-section (1) shall be apportioned among`
  line `all the intermediaries having a share or interest in the estate in the proportion of their shares or interest,`
  line `and if in doing so, any dispute involving a question of title arises, the compensation officer shall refer the`
  line `parties to a civil court.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section except clause (b) (ii) of sub-section (1), "previous year"`
  line `means the year immediately preceding the year in which the vesting date falls.`
obj_root_law_sections_145_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_146:
  sectionId (37970)
  sectionNo (146)
  orderNo 146
  title `Compensation payable to intermediary.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_146_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37970&sectionno=146&orderno=146&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_146_content:
  string
  line `(1) The compensation payable to an intermediary`
  line `shall be a multiple of his net income from the estate or where the intermediary has shares or interests in`
  line `two or more estates, of the aggregate of his net incomes from all such estates, in accordance with the`
  line `following table, namely:--`
  line
  line `Amount of net income Total compensation payable`
  line
  line `(a) Where the net income does not exceed Rs.1,000. Fifteen times such net income.`
  line
  line `(b) Where the net income exceeds Rs. 1,000 but Twelve times such net income or the`
  line `does not exceed Rs. 2,500. maximum amount under (a) above,`
  line `whichever is greater.`
  line
  line `(c) Where the net income exceeds Rs. 2,500 but Eleven times such net income or the`
  line `does not exceed Rs. 5,000. maximum amount under (b) above,`
  line `whichever is greater.`
  line
  line `(d) Where the net income exceeds Rs. 5,000 Ten times such net income or the maximum`
  line `but does not exceed Rs. 7,500. amount under (c) above, whichever is`
  line greater.
  line
  line `(e) Where the net income exceeds Rs. 7,500 Nine times such net income or the maximum`
  line `but does not exceed Rs. 10,000. amount under (d) above, whichever is greater.`
  line
  line `Amount of net income Total compensation payable`
  line
  line `(f) Where the net income exceeds Rs. 10,000 Eight times such net income or the maximum`
  line `but does not exceed Rs. 15,000. amount under (e) above, whichever is greater.`
  line
  line `(g) Where the net income exceeds Rs. 15,000 Seven times such net income or the maximum`
  line `but does not exceed Rs. 30,000. amount under (f) above, whichever is greater.`
  line
  line `(h) Where the net income exceeds Rs. 30,000 Six times such net income or the maximum`
  line `but does not exceed Rs. 50,000, amount under (g) above, whichever is greater.`
  line
  line `(i) Where the net income exceeds Rs. 50,000 Five times such net income or the maximum`
  line `amount but does not exceed Rs. 1,00,000. amount under (h) above, whichever is greater.`
  line
  line `(j) Where the net income exceeds Rs. 1,00,000 Three times such net income or the maximum`
  line `but does not exceed Rs. 3,00,000. amount under (i) above, whichever is greater.`
  line
  line `(k) Where the net income exceeds Rs. 3,00,000. Two times such net income or the maximum`
  line `amount under (j) above, whichever, is greater.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the net income or any portion of the net income from an estate is dedicated exclusively to`
  line `charitable or religious purposes, the compensation payable in respect of such net income or portion shall,`
  line `instead of being assessed under sub-section (1), be assessed as a perpetual annuity equal to such net`
  line `income or portion, as the case may be, payable in the prescribed manner for those purposes.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section, if the salary, remuneration or any allowance`
  line `payable to the Mutawalli of a wakf or the shebait of a Hindu temple or a trustee of any other charitable or`
  line `religious trust does not exceed 15 per cent. of the net income, then such net income shall be deemed to be`
  line `dedicated exclusively to charitable or religious purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_146_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_147:
  sectionId (37971)
  sectionNo (147)
  orderNo 147
  title `Disposal of claims of creditors.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_147_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37971&sectionno=147&orderno=147&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_147_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator shall appoint a claims officer not`
  line `below the rank of sub-judge to dispose of the claims of creditors whose debts are secured by a mortgage`
  line `of or charge on any estate or part thereof vested in the Government under section 134 and to discharge`
  line `any other duties assigned to him by this Act or the rules made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) Every creditor referred to in sub-section (1) shall prefer his claim in writing before the claims`
  line `officer in the manner and with-in the time prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The claims officer shall inquire into the claims in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed`
  line `and determine the amount to which each of the creditors is entitled.`
  line
  line `(4) Where there are two or more creditors, the claims officer shall determine, in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the Transfer of Property Act, 1882 (4 of 1882), the order in which each such creditor is`
  line `entitled to receive the amount due to him.`
obj_root_law_sections_147_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_148:
  sectionId (37972)
  sectionNo (148)
  orderNo 148
  title `Appeal against the decision of claims officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_148_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37972&sectionno=148&orderno=148&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_148_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order of the`
  line `claims officer may, within sixty days of the date of the order, prefer an appeal to the District Judge having`
  line jurisdiction.
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the District Judge on appeal, or of the claims officer where no appeal is preferred,`
  line `shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_148_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_149:
  sectionId (37973)
  sectionNo (149)
  orderNo 149
  title `Preliminary publication of compensation assessment roll and disposal of objections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_149_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37973&sectionno=149&orderno=149&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_149_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the amount of compensation has been determined in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of section 146 and entered in the compensation assessment roll, the compensation officer shall`
  line `cause a draft of such roll to be published in the prescribed manner and for the prescribed period. The`
  line `compensation officer shall send copies of the relevant portions of the draft roll to the intermediaries`
  line `concerned and shall receive and consider any objections which may be made within three months of the`
  line `receipt of such copy to any entry therein or to any omission therefrom. The compensation officer shall`
  line `dispose of such objections in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(2) Separate draft compensation assessment rolls may be prepared and published under`
  line `sub-section (1) for different villages or groups of villages.`
obj_root_law_sections_149_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_150:
  sectionId (37974)
  sectionNo (150)
  orderNo 150
  title `Contents of the order of compensation officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_150_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37974&sectionno=150&orderno=150&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_150_content:
  string
  line `Every order of the compensation officer`
  line `deciding an objection under sub-section (1) of section 149 shall contain a concise statement of the case,`
  line `the points for determination, the decision thereon and the reasons for such decision.`
obj_root_law_sections_150_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_151:
  sectionId (37975)
  sectionNo (151)
  orderNo 151
  title `Appeals against order of compensation officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_151_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37975&sectionno=151&orderno=151&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_151_content:
  string
  line `(1) From every order passed by a`
  line `compensation officer under section 150, an appeal shall lie to a Special Judge appointed for the purpose,`
  line `within ninety days of the date of the order.`
  line
  line `(2) An appeal shall lie to the court of the Judicial Commissioner, from every order passed on appeal`
  line `by a Special Judge under sub-section (1), within sixty days of the passing of such order, on any of the`
  line `grounds specified in section 100 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
  line
  line `(3) The decision of the Judicial Commissioner, or of the Special Judge where no second appeal is`
  line `preferred, or of the compensation officer where no appeal to the Special Judge is preferred, shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_151_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_152:
  sectionId (37976)
  sectionNo (152)
  orderNo 152
  title `Final publication of the compensation assessment roll.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_152_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37976&sectionno=152&orderno=152&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_152_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where no objection or appeal has`
  line `been filed or all the objections and appeals filed have been finally disposed of, the compensation officer`
  line `shall cause the draft compensation assessment roll to be finally published, or make such alterations in the`
  line `draft compensation assessment roll as may be necessary to give effect to any order passed on objection`
  line `made under sub-section (1) of section 149 or on appeal under section 151 and cause the roll as so altered`
  line `to be finally published, in the prescribed manner together with a certificate stating the fact of such final`
  line `publication and the date thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) The publication of the compensation assessment roll under sub-section (1) shall be conclusive`
  line `evidence that the said roll has been duly made under this Chapter and every entry in such roll shall, save`
  line `as otherwise provided in this Act, be conclusive evidence of the matters referred to in such entry.`
obj_root_law_sections_152_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_153:
  sectionId (37977)
  sectionNo (153)
  orderNo 153
  title `Correction of bona fide mistakes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_153_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37977&sectionno=153&orderno=153&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_153_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Correction of the compensation assessment roll`
  line `after it has been finally published under section 152 shall be made except as provided in this section.`
  line
  line `(2) Correction of bona fide mistakes or corrections necessitated by succession to or inheritance of any`
  line `interest in the estate can be made by the compensation officer at any time before the payment of`
  line `compensation, either of his own motion or on the application of the person interested, but no such`
  line `correction shall be made while any legal proceeding affecting such entry is pending.`
  line
  line `(3) Every time a correction is made under sub-section (2), the compensation officer shall cause a draft`
  line `of the correction to be published in the same manner as the draft compensation, assessment roll, and after`
  line `considering and disposing of any objections that may be made, shall cause the correction to be finally`
  line published.
obj_root_law_sections_153_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_154:
  sectionId (37978)
  sectionNo (154)
  orderNo 154
  title `Ad interim payment of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_154_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37978&sectionno=154&orderno=154&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_154_content:
  string
  line `After the vesting date and before the final publication`
  line `of the compensation assessment roll, ad interim payment to the outgoing intermediary may be made as`
  line `follows:--`
  line
  line `(a) the compensation officer shall calculate the probable amount of compensation payable to him;`
  line
  line `(b) two and a half per cent. of such probable amount shall be paid ad interim to each intermediary`
  line `in cash every year until such time as the compensation assessment roll is finally published;`
  line
  line `(c) if there is any dispute as to the title of any person to receive the amount or as to the`
  line `apportionment of it, the amount shall be kept in deposit in the manner prescribed until the dispute is`
  line `finally determined; and on such determination, the compensation officer shall pay the amount or the`
  line `portion thereof to the person or persons entitled to receive the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_154_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_155:
  sectionId (37979)
  sectionNo (155)
  orderNo 155
  title `Mode of payment of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_155_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37979&sectionno=155&orderno=155&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_155_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the compensation assessment roll has been`
  line `finally published, the compensation officer shall deduct from the amount shown in such roll as payable to`
  line `an intermediary or any other person having interest in the estate, the following amounts namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) ad interim payments made under section 154;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount, if any, the deduction of which has been ordered under section 135;`
  line
  line `(c) the amounts payable to creditors as determined by the claims officer.`
  line
  line `(2) The balance remaining after the deductions referred to in sub-section (1) are made shall be given`
  line `in cash, in one lump sum or in annual instalments not exceeding twenty, or in bonds, or partly in cash and`
  line `partly in bonds, in accordance with such rules as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The bonds referred to in sub-section (2) may be either negotiable or non-negotiable, and`
  line `transferable in such circumstances and in such manner as may be prescribed and shall carry interest at the`
  line `rate of two and a half per cent. per annum on the amount outstanding thereon, with effect from the date of`
  line issue.
  line
  line `(4) If any dispute, arises as to the title of any person to receive the, amount or as to the apportionment`
  line `of it, the compensation officer may, if he thinks fit, keep the amount of compensation or the bonds`
  line `referred to above in deposit in the manner prescribed, until the dispute is finally determined; and on such`
  line `determination, the compensation officer shall pay the amount or the portions thereof to the person or`
  line `persons entitled to receive the same.`
obj_root_law_sections_155_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_156:
  sectionId (37980)
  sectionNo (156)
  orderNo 156
  title `Compensation due to maintenance holder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_156_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37980&sectionno=156&orderno=156&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_156_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person claiming as maintenance holder`
  line `to be entitled to any portion of the compensation awarded to any intermediary under this Chapter applies`
  line `to the compensation officer for payment of the same to him, the compensation officer may, with the`
  line `consent of the intermediary, direct the payment to the applicant out of the compensation of such amount`
  line `as the intermediary may have agreed to be paid to the applicant, and any such payment shall be a valid`
  line `discharge of the liability of the Government in respect of the amount so paid.`
  line
  line `(2) If the intermediary does not give his consent, the compensation officer shall direct the applicant to`
  line `file, within three months, a suit or other proceeding in the court having jurisdiction to establish his claim`
  line `and order that the amount claimed shall, not in the meantime be paid to the intermediary.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government shall not be made a party to any suit or proceeding instituted or commenced in`
  line `pursuance of any direction given under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) If the suit or proceeding referred to in sub-section (2) is instituted or commenced within the period`
  line `aforesaid, the compensation officer shall place the amount claimed at the disposal of the court before`
  line `which such suit or proceeding is instituted.`
  line
  line `(5) If the suit or proceeding is not instituted or commenced within the period of three months`
  line `aforesaid, the compensation officer shall order the amount to be paid to the intermediary.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section, a maintenance holder means a person entitled to`
  line `receive maintenance under a registered deed, decree or order of court.`
obj_root_law_sections_156_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_157:
  sectionId (37981)
  sectionNo (157)
  orderNo 157
  title `Compensation due to person incompetent to alienate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_157_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37981&sectionno=157&orderno=157&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_157_content:
  string
  line `If any intermediary entitled to receive`
  line `compensation in respect of any interest is a person incompetent to alienate such interest, the`
  line `compensation officer shall keep the amount of compensation payable, in respect of such interest, whether`
  line `in cash or in bonds, in deposit with the Collector who shall arrange to invest the cash or the income from`
  line `the bonds in the purchase of such Government or other approved securities as the Collector thinks fit and`
  line `shall direct the payment of the income from such investment to the intermediary who would for the time`
  line `being have been entitled to hold and enjoy such interest if it had not vested in the Government; and such`
  line `cash, bonds and securities shall remain so deposited until they are made over to any person or persons`
  line `becoming absolutely entitled thereto:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing herein contained shall affect the liability of any person who may receive the`
  line `whole or any part of any compensation under this section to pay the same to the person lawfully entitled`
  line thereto.
obj_root_law_sections_157_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_158:
  sectionId (37982)
  sectionNo (158)
  orderNo 158
  title `Inquiries to be judicial proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_158_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37982&sectionno=158&orderno=158&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_158_content:
  string
  line `The Collector, the compensation officer and the claims`
  line `officer, for the purposes of any inquiries or proceedings under this Part, shall have the same powers as are`
  line `vested in a court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of--`
  line
  line `(a) enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath or affirmation;`
  line
  line `(b) compelling the production of documents; and`
  line
  line `(c) issuing commission for the examination of witnesses;`
  line
  line `and such inquiries or proceedings shall be deemed to be judicial proceedings within the meaning of`
  line `sections 193 and 228 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_158_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_159:
  sectionId (37983)
  sectionNo (159)
  orderNo 159
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_159_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37983&sectionno=159&orderno=159&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_159_content:
  string
  line Whoever--
  line
  line `(a) wilfully fails or neglects to comply with any requirements made of him under this Part, or`
  line
  line `(b) contravenes any lawful order passed under this Part, or`
  line
  line `(c) obstructs or resists the taking by the Collector or any other officer authorized by him in`
  line `writing of charge of any property which is vested in the Government under this Part, or`
  line
  line `(d) furnishes information which he knows or believes to be false or does not believe to be true,`
  line
  line `shall, on conviction before a Magistrate, be punishable with fine which may extend to five hundred`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_159_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_160:
  sectionId (37984)
  sectionNo (160)
  orderNo 160
  title `Application of Part III to persons becoming raiyats or under-raiyats under Part IV.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_160_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37984&sectionno=160&orderno=160&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_160_content:
  string
  line `Where, as a result of the operation of this Part, any person acquires the right to hold land either`
  line `as a raiyat or an under-raiyat, the provisions of Part III shall as far as may be, apply to the determination`
  line `of such right and in such application, any reference in the said Part to the commencement of this Act shall`
  line `be construed as a reference to the vesting date.`
obj_root_law_sections_160_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_161:
  sectionId (37985)
  sectionNo (161)
  orderNo 161
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_161_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37985&sectionno=161&orderno=161&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_161_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for the purpose of carrying out the purposes of this Part.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner of publication of a notification under section 134;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed and the forms to be adopted in inquiries and proceedings under`
  line `this Part;`
  line
  line `(c) the mode of service of any order, notice or other documents under this Part;`
  line
  line `(d) the form of the statements to be furnished by intermediaries;`
  line
  line `(e) the inspection of and making notes from documents, registers and records under section 137,`
  line `the grant of certified copies thereof and the fee to be charged for such grant;`
  line
  line `(f) the form and the manner in which compensation assessment rolls shall be prepared and the`
  line `particulars to be mentioned therein;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of apportionment of net income among intermediaries;`
  line
  line `(h) the procedure to be followed in the case of intermediaries having shares or interest in different`
  line estates;
  line
  line `(i) the manner in which the preliminary and the final publication of the compensation assessment`
  line `roll shall be made;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of determining the amount of annuities payable to religious and charitable`
  line `institutions and the procedure for making payments;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner in which the income of the previous year shall be determined;`
  line
  line `(l) the determination of the amount of ad interim compensation;`
  line
  line `(m) The manner in which and the period within which creditors may prefer their claims before the`
  line `claims officer and the procedure to be followed in the disposal of such claims;`
  line
  line `(n) the manner in which objections shall be submitted to the compensation officer and the`
  line `procedure to be followed in the disposal of such objections;`
  line
  line `(o) the manner of determining the commuted value of rents under section 145;`
  line
  line `(p) the manner of preferring appeals under Chapters XI and XII;`
  line
  line `(q) the manner of keeping in deposit the amount of compensation under sections 155 and 157;`
  line
  line `(r) the form and contents of bonds;`
  line
  line `(s) the manner in which, and the circumstances under which, bonds shall be transferable, and`
  line
  line `(t) any other matter which is to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_161_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_162:
  sectionId (37986)
  sectionNo (162)
  orderNo 162
  title Exemptions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_162_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37986&sectionno=162&orderno=162&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_162_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to land owned by the Government`
  line `or a local authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_162_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_163:
  sectionId (37987)
  sectionNo (163)
  orderNo 163
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_163_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37987&sectionno=163&orderno=163&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_163_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Chapter,--`
  line
  line `(a) "ceiling limit", in relation to land, means the limit fixed under section 164;`
  line
  line `(b) "family", relation to a person, means the person, the wife or husband, as the case may be, and`
  line `the dependent children and grand-children, of such person;`
  line
  line `(c) "land" does not include land used for non-agricultural purposes.`
obj_root_law_sections_163_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_164:
  sectionId (37988)
  sectionNo (164)
  orderNo 164
  title `Cellings on holdings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_164_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37988&sectionno=164&orderno=164&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_164_content:
  string
  line `No person either by himself or, if he has a family, together with any`
  line `other member of his family (hereinafter referred to as the person representing the family) shall, whether`
  line `as a raiyat or an under-raiyat or as a mortgagee with possession or otherwise, or partly in one capacity and`
  line `partly in another, hold land in excess of twenty-five standard acres in the aggregate:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the number of members of the family of such person exceeds five, he may hold`
  line `five additional standard acres for each member in excess of five, so, however, as not to exceed fifty`
  line `standard acres in the aggregate.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In the case of a company, an association or any other body of individuals, the ceiling`
  line `limit shall be twenty-five standard acres.`
obj_root_law_sections_164_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_165:
  sectionId (37989)
  sectionNo (165)
  orderNo 165
  title `Submission of returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_165_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37989&sectionno=165&orderno=165&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_165_content:
  string
  line `Every person representing a family who at the commencement of this`
  line `Act holds, or has at any time during the period between the 10th day of August, 1957 and such`
  line `commencement held, land in excess of the ceiling limit shall submit to the competent authority, in such`
  line `form and within such time as may be prescribed, a return giving the particulars of all land held by him`
  line `and indicating therein the parcels of land, not exceeding the ceiling limit, which he desires to retain:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a joint holding, all co-sharers may submit the return jointly indicating the`
  line `parcels of land, not exceeding the aggregate of their individual ceiling limits, which they desire to retain.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In the case of a person under disability, the return shall be furnished by his guardian or`
  line `authorised agent, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_165_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_166:
  sectionId (37990)
  sectionNo (166)
  orderNo 166
  title `Collection of information through other agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_166_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37990&sectionno=166&orderno=166&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_166_content:
  string
  line `If any person, who under section 165 is`
  line `required to submit a return, fails to do so, the competent authority may collect the necessary information`
  line `through such agency as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_166_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_167:
  sectionId (37991)
  sectionNo (167)
  orderNo 167
  title `Procedure for determination of excess land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_167_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37991&sectionno=167&orderno=167&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_167_content:
  string
  line `(1) On-receipt of any return under section 165`
  line `or information under section 166 or otherwise, the competent authority shall, after giving the persons`
  line `affected an opportunity of being heard, hold an inquiry in such manner as may be prescribed, and having`
  line `regard to the provisions of section 168 and section 169 or of any rules that may be made in this behalf, it`
  line `shall determine.--`
  line
  line `(a) the total area of land held by each person representing the family;`
  line
  line `(b) the specific parcels of land which he may retain;`
  line
  line `(c) the land held by him in excess of the ceiling limit;`
  line
  line `(d) whether such excess land is held by him as a raiyat or as an under-raiyat or as a mortgagee`
  line `with possession;`
  line
  line `(e) the excess land in respect of which the under-raiyat or the mortgagee with possession may`
  line `acquire the rights of the raiyat or the mortgagor, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(f) the excess land which may be restored to a raiyat or a mortgagor;`
  line
  line `(g) the excess land which shall vest in the Government; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of determining the excess land under this section, any land transferred at any`
  line `time during the period between the 10th day of August, 1957 and the commencement of this Act shall,`
  line `notwithstanding such transfer, be deemed to be held by the transferor.`
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority shall prepare a list in the prescribed form containing the particulars`
  line `determined by him under sub-section (1) and shall cause every such list to be published in the Official`
  line `Gazette and also in such other manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_167_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_168:
  sectionId (37992)
  sectionNo (168)
  orderNo 168
  title `Selection of excess land in cases of certain transfers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_168_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37992&sectionno=168&orderno=168&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_168_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any person holding land in`
  line `excess of the ceiling limit at any time during the period between the 10th day of August, 1957 and the 2nd`
  line `day of December, 1959, has transferred during such period any part of his land to any other person under`
  line `a registered deed for valuable consideration, the excess land to be determined under section 167 shall, to`
  line `the extent possible, be selected out of the land held at the commencement of this Act by the transferor in`
  line `excess of a family holding and no land shall be selected out of the land transferred.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person holding land in excess of the ceiling limit at any time--`
  line
  line `(a) during the period between the 10th day of August, 1957 and the 2nd day of December, 1959,`
  line `has transferred during such period any part of his land to any other person in any manner other than`
  line `under a registered deed for valuable consideration, or`
  line
  line `(b) during the period between the 2nd day of December, 1959 and the commencement of this Act`
  line `has transferred during such period any part of his land to any other person in any manner whatsoever,`
  line
  line `the excess land to be determined under section 167 shall be selected out of the lands held at the`
  line `commencement of this Act by the transferor and the transferee in the same proportion as the land held by`
  line `the transferor bears to the land transferred and where no land is held by the transferor, out of the land`
  line transferred.
  line
  line `(3) Where excess land is to be selected out of the lands of more than one transferee, such land shall be`
  line `selected out of the lands held by each of the transferees in the same proportion as the area of the land`
  line `transferred to him bears to the total area of the lands transferred to all the transferees.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any excess land is selected out of the land transferred, the transfer of such land shall be`
  line void.
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything hereinbefore contained, the excess land to be selected shall in no case`
  line `include the homestead land of a person.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, "homestead land" means the land on which the`
  line `homestead (whether used by the owner or let out on rent) stands together with any courtyard, compound`
  line `and attached garden, not exceeding one acre in the aggregate.`
obj_root_law_sections_168_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_169:
  sectionId (37993)
  sectionNo (169)
  orderNo 169
  title `Excess land to vest in Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_169_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37993&sectionno=169&orderno=169&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_169_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any excess land of a raiyat is in his actual`
  line `possession, the excess land shall vest in the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any excess land of a raiyat is in the possession of a person holding the same as an`
  line `under-raiyat or as a mortgagee and the excess land together with any other land held by such person`
  line `exceeds his ceiling limit, the land in excess of the ceiling limit shall vest in the Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any excess land of a raiyat is in the possession of a person holding the same as an`
  line `under-raiyat or as a mortgagee and such person is allowed to retain the excess land or a part thereof as`
  line `being within his ceiling limit, that person shall acquire the rights of the raiyat or of the mortgagor, as the`
  line `case may be, in respect of such excess land or part thereof on payment of compensation, if any, as`
  line `hereinafter provided, but if that person refuses to pay such compensation, the excess land or part thereof`
  line `shall vest in the Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Where there is any excess land of an under-raiyat or of a mortgagee with possession, the excess`
  line `land shall vest in the Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any case where the excess land or any part thereof held by the raiyat or the`
  line `mortgagor together with any other land held by such person does not exceed the ceiling limit, the excess`
  line `land or such part thereof as does not exceed the ceiling limit shall be restored to the possession of that`
  line `person on an application made by him in this behalf to the competent authority within such time as may`
  line `be prescribed and in the case where the possession of such land is restored to the mortgagor, the mortgage`
  line `in respect of such land shall be deemed to be a simple mortgage.`
obj_root_law_sections_169_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_170:
  sectionId (37994)
  sectionNo (170)
  orderNo 170
  title `Publication of the final list and consequences thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_170_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37994&sectionno=170&orderno=170&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_170_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an entry`
  line `in the list published under sub-section (3) of section 167 may, within thirty days from the date of`
  line `publication thereof in the Official Gazette, file objections thereto before the Collector.`
  line
  line `(2) The Collector or any other officer authorised in this behalf by the Administrator may, after`
  line `considering the objections and after giving the objector or his representatives an opportunity of being`
  line `heard in the matter, approve or modify the list.`
  line
  line `(3) The list as approved or modified under sub-section (2) shall then be published in the Official`
  line `Gazette and also in such other manner as may be prescribed and subject to the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `list shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) With effect from the date of the publication of the list in the Official Gazette under`
  line `sub-section (3),--`
  line
  line `(a) the excess land shall stand transferred to and vest in the Government free of all encumbrances;`
  line or
  line
  line `(b) the possession of the excess land shall stand restored to the raiyat or the mortgagor, as the`
  line `case may be; or`
  line
  line `(c) the rights of the raiyat or the mortgagor in respect of the excess land shall stand transferred to`
  line `the under-raiyat or the mortgagee, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_170_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_171:
  sectionId (37995)
  sectionNo (171)
  orderNo 171
  title Compensation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_171_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37995&sectionno=171&orderno=171&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_171_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any excess land of a raiyat vests in the Government there shall be`
  line `paid by the Government to the raiyat compensation, subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), of an`
  line `amount equal to twenty times the net annual income from such land.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-section (1), the net annual income from any land shall be`
  line `deemed to be one-fifth of the value of the average yearly gross produce of the land, calculated in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Where such excess land or any part thereof is in the possession of an under-raiyat, the`
  line `compensation payable under sub- section (1) in respect of the land shall be apportioned between the raiyat`
  line `and the under-raiyat in such proportion as may be determined by the competent authority in the`
  line `prescribed manner, having regard to their respective shares in the net income from such land.`
  line
  line `(3) In addition to the compensation payable in respect of any excess land under sub-section (1), there`
  line `shall also be paid compensation in respect of any structure or building constructed on such land and any`
  line `trees planted thereon and such compensation shall be determined by the competent authority in the`
  line `prescribed manner, having regard to the market value of such structure or building or the value of such`
  line `trees, and such compensation shall be paid to the person who has constructed the structure or building or`
  line `planted the trees.`
  line
  line `(4) Where any excess land in respect of which compensation is payable is subject to any mortgage or`
  line `other encumbrance, the amount due under the mortgage or other encumbrance in respect of such excess`
  line `land, or where a transfer in respect of any excess land is void by virtue of sub-section (4) of section 168,`
  line `the consideration money paid by the transferee in respect of such excess land, shall be a charge on the`
  line `compensation payable in respect of the excess land to the person who has created the mortgage or`
  line `encumbrance or, as the case may be, to the transferor.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an under-raiyat acquires the rights of a raiyat in respect of any excess land, the`
  line `compensation payable by him in respect of that land shall be equal to the amount which the raiyat would`
  line `have been paid as compensation under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) if the land had vested in the`
  line `Government; and the amount shall, in the first instance, be paid to the raiyat by the Government and shall`
  line `be recovered from the under-raiyat in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(6) Where a mortgagee in possession acquires the rights of the mortgagor in respect of any excess`
  line `land under sub-section (3) of section 169, the compensation payable by the mortgagee in respect of that`
  line `land shall be such sum of money, if any, as may be due to the mortgagor after setting off the mortgage`
  line `debt against the market value of such excess land.`
  line
  line `(7) Where any excess land of a religious or charitable institution vests in the Government,`
  line `such institution shall, in lieu of compensation payable under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), or`
  line `sub-section (3), be paid an annuity equal to the net annual income of the excess land and such net annual`
  line `income shall be determined by the competent authority in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(8) The competent authority shall, after holding an inquiry in the prescribed manner, make an order`
  line `determining the amount of compensation payable to any person under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_171_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_172:
  sectionId (37996)
  sectionNo (172)
  orderNo 172
  title `Manner of payment of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_172_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37996&sectionno=172&orderno=172&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_172_content:
  string
  line `(1) The compensation payable under section 171 shall`
  line `be due from the date of the publication of the list under sub-section (3) of section 170 and may be paid in`
  line `cash, in a lump sum or in instalments, or in bonds.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the compensation is payable in bonds, the bonds may be made not transferable or`
  line `transferable by endorsement or in any other manner but all such bonds shall be redeemed within such`
  line `period, not exceeding twenty years from the date of issue, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where there is any delay in the payment of compensation or where the compensation is paid`
  line `either in instalments or in bonds, it shall carry interest at the rate of two and a half per cent. per annum`
  line `from the date on which it falls due.`
obj_root_law_sections_172_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_173:
  sectionId (37997)
  sectionNo (173)
  orderNo 173
  title `Limit of future acquisition of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_173_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37997&sectionno=173&orderno=173&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_173_content:
  string
  line `No person representing a family shall acquire in any`
  line `manner whatsoever, whether by transfer, exchange, lease, agreement or succession, any land where such`
  line `acquisition has the effect of making the total area of the land held by him exceed the ceiling limit; and`
  line `any such land in excess of the ceiling limit shall be treated as excess land of the transferee and the`
  line `provisions of sections 167 to 172 shall, as far as may be, apply to such excess land.`
obj_root_law_sections_173_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_174:
  sectionId (37998)
  sectionNo (174)
  orderNo 174
  title `Excess land not to be surrendered in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_174_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37998&sectionno=174&orderno=174&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_174_content:
  string
  line `Where a person representing a family`
  line `holds land not exceeding the ceiling limit, but subsequently the land held exceeds the ceiling limit, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, such person shall not be required to surrender any`
  line `part of the land on the ground that it is excess land, if such excess is due to any improvements effected in`
  line `the land by the efforts of the family or to a decrease in the number of its members.`
obj_root_law_sections_174_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_175:
  sectionId (37999)
  sectionNo (175)
  orderNo 175
  title `Power of Collector to take possession of excess land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_175_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=37999&sectionno=175&orderno=175&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_175_content:
  string
  line `After the publication of the list of`
  line `excess land under sub-section (3) of section 170, and after demarcation in the prescribed manner of such`
  line `land where necessary, the Collector may take possession of any excess land and may use or cause to be`
  line `used such force as may be necessary for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_175_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_176:
  sectionId (38000)
  sectionNo (176)
  orderNo 176
  title `Offences and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_176_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38000&sectionno=176&orderno=176&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_176_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever being bound to submit a return under section 165 fails to`
  line `do so, without reasonable cause, within the prescribed time, or submits a return which he knows or has`
  line `reason to believe to be false, shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever contravenes any lawful order made under this Chapter or otherwise obstructs any person`
  line `from lawfully taking possession of any land shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_176_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_177:
  sectionId (38001)
  sectionNo (177)
  orderNo 177
  title `Finality of orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_177_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38001&sectionno=177&orderno=177&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_177_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, every order made under this Chapter`
  line `shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_177_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_178:
  sectionId (38002)
  sectionNo (178)
  orderNo 178
  title `Power to exempt, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_178_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38002&sectionno=178&orderno=178&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_178_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, on an application made to him in this`
  line `behalf within three months from the commencement of this Act, exempt from the operation of section`
  line 164--
  line
  line `(a) any land which is being used for growing tea, coffee or rubber including lands used or`
  line `required for use for purposes ancillary to, or for the extension of, the cultivation of tea, coffee or`
  line `rubber to be determined in the prescribed manner;`
  line
  line `(b) any sugarcane farm operated by a sugar factory;`
  line
  line `(c) any specialised farm which is being used for cattle breeding, dairy or wool raising;`
  line
  line `(d) any person who holds a compact block of land exceeding the ceiling limit which--`
  line
  line `(i) is being used as an orchard from before the 1st January, 1958; or`
  line
  line `(ii) is being used as a farm in which heavy investment or permanent structural improvements`
  line `have been made and which, in the opinion of the Administrator, is being so efficiently managed`
  line `that its break up is likely to bring a fall in production:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person holds the compact block of land together with any other land, he`
  line `shall be permitted to elect to retain either the compact block of land, notwithstanding that it exceeds the`
  line `ceiling limit or the other land not exceeding the ceiling limit;`
  line
  line `(e) any land which is being held by a co-operative society, provided that where a member of any`
  line `such society holds a share in such land, his share shall be taken into account in determining his`
  line `ceiling limit:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Administrator may entertain the application after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `three months, if he is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by sufficient cause from making the`
  line `application in time.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any land in respect of which exemption has been granted to a person under clause (d) of`
  line `sub-section (1) is transferred to another person, the Administrator may, on an application made to him`
  line `within three months from the date of the transfer, exempt the transferee from the operation of section 164`
  line `and section 173 and the provisions of the said clause shall, as far as may be, apply to the grant of such`
  line exemption.
  line
  line `(3) Where the Administrator is of opinion that the use of land for any specified purpose is expedient`
  line `or necessary in the public interest, he may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make a declaration to`
  line `that effect and on the issue of such notification, any person may, notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 173, acquire land in excess of the ceiling limit for being used for such specified purpose and such`
  line `person shall, within one month from the date of such acquisition, send intimation thereof to the competent`
  line authority.
  line
  line `(4) Where any land, in respect of which exemption has been granted under sub-section (1) or`
  line `sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), ceases to be used, or is not within the prescribed time used, for the`
  line `purpose for which exemption had been granted, the Administrator may, after giving the persons affected`
  line `an opportunity of being heard, withdraw such exemption.`
obj_root_law_sections_178_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_179:
  sectionId (38003)
  sectionNo (179)
  orderNo 179
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_179_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38003&sectionno=179&orderno=179&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_179_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Chapter,--`
  line
  line `(a) "holding" means the aggregate area of land held by a person as a raiyat;`
  line
  line `(b) "fragment" means a holding of less than two standard acres in area;`
  line
  line `(c) "land" has the same meaning as in Chapter XIII.`
obj_root_law_sections_179_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_180:
  sectionId (38004)
  sectionNo (180)
  orderNo 180
  title `Restrictions on transfer, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_180_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38004&sectionno=180&orderno=180&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_180_content:
  string
  line `(1) No portion of a holding shall be transferred by way of sale,`
  line `exchange, gift, bequest or mortgage with possession, so as to create a fragment:`
  line
  line `Provided that the provisions of this sub-section shall not apply to a gift made in favour of the`
  line `Bhoodan movement initiated by Acharya Vinoba Bhave.`
  line
  line `(2) No portion of a holding shall be transferred by way of lease, where as a result of such lease,--`
  line
  line `(i) the lessor shall be left with less than two standard acres, or`
  line
  line `(ii) the total area held by the lessee exceeds the limit of a family holding.`
  line
  line `(3) No fragment shall be transferred to a person who does not have some land under personal`
  line `cultivation or to a person who holds, or by reason of such transfer shall hold, land in excess of the limit of`
  line `a family holding.`
obj_root_law_sections_180_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_181:
  sectionId (38005)
  sectionNo (181)
  orderNo 181
  title `Partition of holding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_181_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38005&sectionno=181&orderno=181&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_181_content:
  string
  line `(1) No holding shall be partitioned in such manner as to create a`
  line fragment.
  line
  line `(2) A fragment shall not be partitioned unless as a result of such partition its portions get merged in`
  line `holdings of two standard acres or more or in fragments so as to create holdings of two standard acres or`
  line more.
  line
  line `(3) Whenever, in a suit for partition, the court finds that the partition of a holding will result in the`
  line `creation of a fragment, the court shall, instead of proceeding to divide the holding, direct the sale of the`
  line `same and distribute the proceeds thereof among the co-sharers.`
  line
  line `(4) Wherever a holding is put up for sale under sub-section (3), a co-sharer shall have the first option`
  line `to purchase the holding at the highest bid; if there are two or more co-sharers claiming the first option,`
  line `that co-sharer who offers the highest consideration shall be preferred.`
obj_root_law_sections_181_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_182:
  sectionId (38006)
  sectionNo (182)
  orderNo 182
  title `Transfers in contravention of this Chapter.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_182_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38006&sectionno=182&orderno=182&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_182_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any transfer, partition or lease of land made`
  line `in contravention of the provisions of this Chapter shall be void.`
  line
  line `(2) No document of transfer, partition or lease of land shall be registered unless declarations in`
  line `writing are made, in such form and manner as may be prescribed, by the parties thereto before the`
  line `competent registering authority under the Indian Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), regarding lands`
  line `held by each prior to the transaction and the land which each shall come to hold thereafter.`
  line
  line `(3) No registering authority shall register under the Indian Registration Act, 1908 (16 of 1908), any`
  line `document of transfer, partition or lease of land if, from the declarations made under sub-section (2), it`
  line `appears that the transaction has been effected in contravention of the provisions of this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_182_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_183:
  sectionId (38007)
  sectionNo (183)
  orderNo 183
  title Penalty.
  content obj_root_law_sections_183_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38007&sectionno=183&orderno=183&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_183_content:
  string
  line `The parties to any transfer, partition or lease made or entered into in contravention of`
  line `any of the provisions of this Chapter shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one hundred`
  line rupees.
obj_root_law_sections_183_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_184:
  sectionId (38008)
  sectionNo (184)
  orderNo 184
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_184_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38008&sectionno=184&orderno=184&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_184_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Part.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form in which, and the period within which, a return under section 165 may be submitted;`
  line
  line `(b) the agency through which information may be collected under section 166;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of holding enquiries under this Part;`
  line
  line `(d) the matters which may be determined under sub-section (1) of section 167 and the manner of`
  line `determination of excess lands under this Part;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which a list under sub-section (3) of section 167 or sub-section (3) of section 170`
  line `may be prepared and the manner of publication of such list;`
  line
  line `(f) the period within which an application for restoration of excess land may be made under the`
  line `proviso to sub-section (4) of section 169;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of apportionment of compensation between the raiyat and the under-raiyat under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 171;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of assessment of the market value of any structure or building or trees under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 171;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of recovery of the compensation payable by the under-raiyat under sub-section (5)`
  line `of section 171;`
  line
  line `(j) the manner of determining under sub-section (6) of section 171 the market value of any excess`
  line `land in respect of which a mortgagee in possession acquires the rights of the mortgagor;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of determination of the net annual income of any excess land for the purpose of`
  line `payment of compensation under section 171;`
  line
  line `(l) The manner of payment of compensation, including the number of instalments in which the`
  line `compensation may be paid or recovered and the period within which bonds may be redeemed;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of demarcation of any excess land under section 175;`
  line
  line `(n) the matters which may be determined by the Administrator in granting an exemption under`
  line `section 178 including the form in which applications and intimations may be made or given, under`
  line `section 178;`
  line
  line `(o) the form of declarations under section 182;`
  line
  line `(p) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_184_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_185:
  sectionId (38009)
  sectionNo (185)
  orderNo 185
  title `Recovery of amount due as arrear of land revenue.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_185_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38009&sectionno=185&orderno=185&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_185_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to any other`
  line `provision of this Act, any amount due to the Government, whether by way of costs, penalty or otherwise,`
  line `and any other amount which is ordered to be paid to or recovered by the Government, under this Act shall`
  line `be recoverable in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_185_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_186:
  sectionId (38010)
  sectionNo (186)
  orderNo 186
  title `Protection against eviction or surrender in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_186_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38010&sectionno=186&orderno=186&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_186_content:
  string
  line `(1) After the commencement of`
  line `this Act and before the vesting date referred to in sub-section (1) of section 134,--`
  line
  line `(a) the provisions of sections 111 to 117 shall, so far as may be, apply to tenants and sub-tenants`
  line `as defined in clause (d) of section 133;`
  line
  line `(b) no such tenant or sub-tenant shall surrender any land held by him as such and no person shall`
  line `enter upon any such land unless such surrender isbona fide and is made with the previous permission`
  line `in writing of the competent authority, and the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 125 shall apply`
  line `to any case where such permission is refused;`
  line
  line `(c) no such tenant or sub-tenant shall, whether in execution of a decree or order of court or`
  line `otherwise, be evicted from any such land on any ground other than those specified in clauses (c) and`
  line
  line `(d) a sub-section (1) of section 118, and any proceeding for eviction of such tenant or sub-tenant on`
  line `any ground other than those specified in the said clauses (c) and (d) pending at such commencement`
  line `shall abate without prejudice to any action that may be taken under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Where, on or after the 10th day of August, 1957 and before the commencement of this Act, any`
  line `such tenant or sub-tenant has surrendered any land held by him as such or been evicted from such land`
  line `and the surrender or eviction could not have taken place if this Act had been in force on the date of such`
  line `surrender or eviction, the competent authority may, either on his own motion or on application made by`
  line `the tenant or sub-tenant in this behalf, restore him to possession of the land which has been surrendered or`
  line `from which he has been evicted.`
obj_root_law_sections_186_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_187:
  sectionId (38011)
  sectionNo (187)
  orderNo 187
  title `Special provision regarding Scheduled Tribes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_187_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38011&sectionno=187&orderno=187&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_187_content:
  string
  line `No transfer of land by a person who is a`
  line `member of the Scheduled Tribes shall be valid unless--`
  line
  line `(a) the transfer is to another member of the Scheduled Tribes; or`
  line
  line `(b) where the transfer is to a person who is not a member of any such tribe, it is made with the`
  line `previous permission in writing of the Collector; or`
  line
  line `(c) the transfer is by way of mortgage to a co-operative society.`
obj_root_law_sections_187_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_188:
  sectionId (38012)
  sectionNo (188)
  orderNo 188
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts excluded.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_188_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38012&sectionno=188&orderno=188&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_188_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other proceeding shall, unless otherwise`
  line `expressly provided in this Act, lie or be instituted in any civil court with respect to any matter arising`
  line `under and provided for by this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that if in a dispute between parties a question of title is involved, a civil suit may be brought`
  line `for the adjudication of such question.`
obj_root_law_sections_188_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_189:
  sectionId (38013)
  sectionNo (189)
  orderNo 189
  title `Act to over-ride contracts and other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_189_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38013&sectionno=189&orderno=189&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_189_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided, the provisions of this`
  line `Act shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law, custom or`
  line `usage or agreement or decree or order of court.`
obj_root_law_sections_189_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_190:
  sectionId (38014)
  sectionNo (190)
  orderNo 190
  title Court-fees.
  content obj_root_law_sections_190_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38014&sectionno=190&orderno=190&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_190_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Courtfees Act, 1870 (7 of 1870), every`
  line `application, appeal or other proceeding under this Act shall bear a court-fee stamp of such value as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_190_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_191:
  sectionId (38015)
  sectionNo (191)
  orderNo 191
  title `Village officers to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_191_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38015&sectionno=191&orderno=191&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_191_content:
  string
  line `Every village accountant and every other village`
  line `officer appointed under this Act shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21`
  line `of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_191_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_192:
  sectionId (38016)
  sectionNo (192)
  orderNo 192
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_192_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38016&sectionno=192&orderno=192&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_192_content:
  string
  line `With the previous approval of the Government, the Administrator may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, exempt any class of lands from all or any of the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_192_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_193:
  sectionId (38017)
  sectionNo (193)
  orderNo 193
  title `General provision as to penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_193_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38017&sectionno=193&orderno=193&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_193_content:
  string
  line `Whoever contravenes any provision of this Act for which`
  line `no penalty has been otherwise provided for therein shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five`
  line `hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_193_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_194:
  sectionId (38018)
  sectionNo (194)
  orderNo 194
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_194_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38018&sectionno=194&orderno=194&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_194_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other proceedings shall lie--`
  line
  line `(a) against any officer of the Government for anything in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) against the Government for any damage caused or likely to be caused or any injury suffered or`
  line `likely to be suffered by anything in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_194_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_195:
  sectionId (38019)
  sectionNo (195)
  orderNo 195
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_195_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38019&sectionno=195&orderno=195&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_195_content:
  string
  line `The Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette delegate`
  line `to any officer or authority subordinate to him any of the powers conferred on him or on any officer`
  line `subordinate to him by this Act, other than the power to make rules, to be exercised subject to such`
  line `restrictions and conditions as may be specified in the said notification.`
obj_root_law_sections_195_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_196:
  sectionId (38020)
  sectionNo (196)
  orderNo 196
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_196_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38020&sectionno=196&orderno=196&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_196_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to any provision of this`
  line `Act, the Government may, as occasion requires, take any action not inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act which may appear to it necessary for the purpose of removing the difficulty.`
obj_root_law_sections_196_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_197:
  sectionId (38021)
  sectionNo (197)
  orderNo 197
  title `General power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_197_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38021&sectionno=197&orderno=197&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_197_content:
  string
  line `Without prejudice to any power to make rules contained`
  line `elsewhere in this Act, the Administrator may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules generally`
  line `to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_197_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_198:
  sectionId (38022)
  sectionNo (198)
  orderNo 198
  title `Laying of rules before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_198_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38022&sectionno=198&orderno=198&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_198_content:
  string
  line `Every rule made under this Act shall be laid as soon as`
  line `may be after it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two successive sessions, and if before the expiry of the`
  line `session in which it is so laid or the session immediately following, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_198_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_199:
  sectionId (38023)
  sectionNo (199)
  orderNo 199
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_199_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_199_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803&sectionId=38023&sectionno=199&orderno=199&orgactid=AC_CEN_18_21_00012_196043_1528449863803
obj_root_law_sections_199_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the date on which any of the provisions of this Act are`
  line `brought into force in any area in the Union territory of Tripura, the enactments specified in the Schedule`
  line `or so much thereof as relate to the matters covered by the provisions so brought into force shall stand`
  line `repealed in such area.`
  line
  line `(2) The repeal of any enactment or part thereof by sub-section (1) shall not affect,--`
  line
  line `(a) the previous operation of such enactment of anything duly done or suffered thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) any right, privilege, obligation or liability acquired, accrued or incurred under such`
  line enactment;
  line
  line `(c) any penalty, for forfeiture or punishment incurred in respect of any offence committed against`
  line `such enactment;`
  line
  line `(d) any investigation, legal proceeding or remedy in respect of any such right, privilege,`
  line `obligation, liability, penalty, forfeiture or punishment as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `and any such investigation, legal proceeding or remedy may be instituted or enforced and any such`
  line `penalty, forfeiture or punishment may be imposed as if such enactment or part thereof had not been`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions contained in sub-section (2), any appointment, rule, order, notification or`
  line `proclamation made or issued, any lease, rent, right or liability granted, fixed, acquired or incurred and any`
  line `other thing done or action taken under any of the enactments or parts thereof repealed, under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall, in so far as it is not inconsistent with the provision of this Act brought into force, be`
  line `deemed to have been made, issued, granted, fixed acquired, incurred, done or taken under this Act and`
  line `shall continue to be in force until superseded by anything done or any action taken under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Any custom or usage prevailing at the time any of the provisions of this Act are brought into force`
  line `in any area in the Union territory of Tripura and having the force of law therein shall, if such custom or`
  line `usage is repugnant to or inconsistent with such provision, cease to be operative to the extent of such`
  line `repugnancy or inconsistency.`
